WEBVTT

00:01.760 --> 00:05.127
[ UP-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYING ]

00:05.170 --> 00:07.638
Oliver: OHHHHH!

00:07.670 --> 00:08.830
[ SCA'ITERED APPLAUSE ]

00:08.870 --> 00:10.633
ALL RIGHT,
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,

00:10.670 --> 00:14.777
NEXT QUESTION -- WHICH ONE
OF YOU IS BETTER AT HOUSEWORK?

00:14.810 --> 00:15.731
IAM.
ME!

00:15.780 --> 00:17.441
OH!
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?

00:17.480 --> 00:20.119
NO. YOUR CLOTHES
ARE ALL OVER MY BEDROOM FLOOR.

00:20.150 --> 00:22.641
OH, I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T KNOW
THAT WAS A PROBLEM.

00:22.690 --> 00:23.645
I CAN MAKE IT STOP.

00:23.690 --> 00:25.180
OHH!

00:25.220 --> 00:26.380
[ Mockingly] "OHH."

00:26.420 --> 00:27.682
[ LAUGHS ]

00:27.720 --> 00:30.154
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
W-WE'LL MOVE PAST THAT.

00:30.190 --> 00:33.421
UH, NEXT QUESTION --
WHO GIVES BETTER GIFI'S?

00:34.400 --> 00:37.563
SHOW US WHAT YOU'VE WON,
MCNALLY.

00:37.600 --> 00:38.624
[ LAUGHS ]

00:38.670 --> 00:39.967
[ Chuckling ]
OKAY. I WILL.

00:40.000 --> 00:41.729
I'M -- I'M JUST GONNA --
HOLD ON.

00:42.910 --> 00:44.901
ALL RIGHT,
PAUSING THE GAME.

00:44.940 --> 00:47.829
AND SAMMY
IS JILTED ON THE HOT SEAT.

00:47.880 --> 00:49.541
HOW'S THAT SIT WITH YOU,
PAL?

00:49.580 --> 00:50.478
IT'S FINE.

00:50.510 --> 00:53.775
GIVE ME A CHANCE
[CLEARS THROAT] TO, UH...

00:53.820 --> 00:55.310
TO ASK YOU A FAVOR.

00:55.350 --> 00:58.547
UH, I WOULD LOVE TO,
BUT I CANNOT BE YOUR LAST FLING.

00:58.590 --> 01:01.582
NO. NOW, AS YOU ALL KNOW,
I'M GETTING MARRIED.

01:01.620 --> 01:03.383
OLIVER...

01:03.430 --> 01:04.488
Crowd: AWW!

01:04.530 --> 01:05.383
[ APPLAUSE ]

01:05.430 --> 01:06.727
...WILL YOU BE
MY BEST MAN?

01:06.760 --> 01:08.455
WILL YOU HAVE ME?

01:08.500 --> 01:09.728
[ LAUGHS ]

01:09.770 --> 01:13.592
I THINK THAT I SEALED THE DEAL
WITH THE WHOLE, UH, YOU KNOW,

01:13.640 --> 01:15.995
"HOW WELL DO YOU KNOW
YOUR PARTNER?" QUIZ.

01:16.040 --> 01:18.929
UH, TOTALLY, BROTHER.
IT WOULD BE MY PLEASURE.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO ASK.

01:18.970 --> 01:20.608
I LOVE YOU.

01:20.640 --> 01:21.834
ANYTIME.

01:21.880 --> 01:22.904
LOVE YOU, TOO, BUDDY.

01:22.950 --> 01:24.303
I'M GONNA GET THIS GUY
A DRINK.

01:24.350 --> 01:26.170
TRACI?

01:26.220 --> 01:28.211
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND.

01:28.250 --> 01:29.911
UH...
GIVE ME A SECOND.

01:29.950 --> 01:31.645
OKAY. IT'S OKAY.

01:34.090 --> 01:35.057
HEY. HEY. HEY. HEY.

01:35.090 --> 01:37.183
HEY, WHAT'S UP?
YOU'RE GIVING ME STRESS FACE.

01:37.230 --> 01:39.425
I-I DON'T KNOW
WHERE MY ENGAGEMENT RING IS.

01:40.330 --> 01:41.524
D-D-DID YOU CHECK
THE BATHROOM?

01:41.560 --> 01:42.265
YES.

01:42.300 --> 01:43.369
POCKETS?
YES.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.061
PURSE?
I DON'T HAVE A PURSE.

01:45.100 --> 01:46.499
WELL, W-WHEN'S
THE LAST TIME YOU SAW IT?

01:46.540 --> 01:47.393
I DON'T KNOW.

01:47.440 --> 01:51.137
UH, SAM'S PLACE? MY PLACE?
UH, THE MALL?

01:51.170 --> 01:52.671
WELL, GOOD
YOU'VE NARROWED IT DOWN.

01:52.710 --> 01:56.202
I CANNOT TELL HIM
THAT I LOST THE RING.

01:56.250 --> 01:57.899
OKAY, OKAY.

01:57.950 --> 02:01.442
Y-- UH, YOU ARE...

02:01.480 --> 02:04.017
HAVING
AN ALLERGIC REACTION.

02:04.050 --> 02:05.017
YES, I AM.
YEAH?

02:05.050 --> 02:08.178
AND ALSO, LIKE, I CAN'T STAY
AT HIS PLACE TONIGHT

02:08.220 --> 02:09.949
BECAUSE I'M...

02:09.990 --> 02:11.526
EXFO-- EXFOLIATING.

02:12.960 --> 02:13.722
SURE. SURE.

02:13.760 --> 02:14.954
SO -- SO, THEN,
UM, WE -- OKAY,

02:15.000 --> 02:18.265
SO AFTER YOUR SHIFT TOMORROW,
WE SCOUR YOUR PLACE, HIS PLACE.

02:18.300 --> 02:19.836
WE BREAK INTO THAT TRUCK
IF WE HAVE TO.

02:19.870 --> 02:23.328
THERE'S NOTHING IN THIS WORLD
THAT ISN'T SOMEWHERE, RIGHT?

02:23.370 --> 02:25.838
YEAH.

02:25.870 --> 02:27.872
***

02:32.720 --> 02:34.176
[ KNOCK ON WINDOW ]

02:35.080 --> 02:35.978
YOU MIND?

02:36.020 --> 02:38.614
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

02:41.190 --> 02:42.179
[ GROANS ]

02:42.230 --> 02:43.458
THANK YOU.

02:43.490 --> 02:45.128
GLAD I CAUGHT YOU.
MM.

02:45.160 --> 02:46.127
COMMISSIONER,
GOOD MORNING.

02:46.160 --> 02:48.720
IS THERE SOMETHING
I CAN HELP YOU WITH, SIR?

02:48.760 --> 02:49.829
YES.

02:49.870 --> 02:52.668
MY STEPSON, DUNCAN,
SAYS THAT THERE'S SOME NEW BLOOD

02:52.700 --> 02:55.089
AT 15 DIVISION --
SOMEONE CALLED WARD.

02:55.140 --> 02:57.506
YES --
OFFICER JULIET WARD.

02:57.540 --> 02:59.371
BUT SHE'S NOT JUST AN OFFICER,
IS SHE?

02:59.410 --> 03:02.208
SEE, I CHECKED.
SHE'S INTERNAL AFFAIRS.

03:02.250 --> 03:03.706
SHE IS.
YES.

03:03.750 --> 03:05.172
I ASSIGNED HER.

03:06.380 --> 03:08.211
UH, IT'S HOT IN HERE.

03:08.250 --> 03:11.515
DO YOU MIND
IF WE...JUST TALK OUTSIDE?

03:16.260 --> 03:17.784
[ SIGHS ]

03:21.300 --> 03:23.791
DID I MISS AN E-MAIL,
WILLIAMS?

03:23.830 --> 03:27.391
WELL, THERE WAS AN EXPLOSION
IN THEIR EVIDENCE ROOM,

03:27.440 --> 03:29.192
AND A LOT OF CASES
WERE BLOWN THAT DAY,

03:29.240 --> 03:30.867
SO IT MADE SENSE
TO PUT SOMEONE IN THERE,

03:30.910 --> 03:33.208
MAKE SURE NONE OF OUR PEOPLE
ALLOWED THAT TO HAPPEN.

03:33.240 --> 03:35.379
I THINK
YOU'RE MISSING THE POINT.

03:35.410 --> 03:37.207
WHY WASN'T I INFORMED?

03:37.250 --> 03:39.673
[ Chuckling ]
WELL, COMMISSIONER...

03:39.720 --> 03:42.780
YOU HIRED ME TO TAKE
THE PRESSURE OFF YOU.

03:42.820 --> 03:43.787
I CAN'T HELP YOU

03:43.820 --> 03:48.052
IF I'M PESTERING YOU
ABOUT EVERY SINGLE DECISION.

03:48.090 --> 03:50.558
DELEGATE, RIGHT?

03:50.590 --> 03:52.490
THAT'S WHAT I'M HERE FOR.

03:52.530 --> 03:54.623
I FIGURED
THAT'S WHAT IT WAS.

03:54.660 --> 03:55.297
MM-HMM.

03:55.330 --> 03:56.365
'CAUSE I AM AN OPTIMIST.

03:56.400 --> 03:58.220
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

03:58.270 --> 04:00.329
I NEED TO SEE A REPORT.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.860
ABSOLUTELY.

04:01.900 --> 04:03.834
JUST GIVE ME A WEEK OR TWO,
PUT IT TOGETHER.

04:03.870 --> 04:06.930
ANYTHING YOU HAVE.
END OF DAY IS FINE.

04:06.980 --> 04:08.470
YES, SIR.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.309
Sam:
SO, HE'S ONTO JULIET.

04:12.350 --> 04:15.672
YOU THINK
HE'S ONTO YOU?

04:15.720 --> 04:16.812
I DON'T KNOW.

04:17.920 --> 04:20.252
BUT HE WANTS A REPORT
AT THE END OF TODAY.

04:20.290 --> 04:22.087
OKAY.
IS THAT A PROBLEM?

04:22.120 --> 04:23.382
YEAH.

04:23.430 --> 04:26.354
BECAUSE,
ACCORDING TO WARD,

04:26.400 --> 04:28.823
THE ONLY OFFICER
WHO COULD HAVE PUT A BOMB

04:28.860 --> 04:31.795
IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM...

04:31.830 --> 04:33.331
IS OLIVER.

04:35.240 --> 04:38.505
YOU GOT TO FIX THIS,
SAMMY.

04:38.540 --> 04:40.508
"MOST LIKELY TO PICK
THE RESTAURANT." YOU.

04:40.540 --> 04:42.508
UH, CRAZY GRILL,
TONIGHT, 8:00, BY THE WAY.
GOOD.

04:42.550 --> 04:44.506
"MOST LIKELY TO REACH
FOR THEIR WALLET." YOU.

04:44.550 --> 04:47.269
"MOST LIKELY TO ACTUALLY PAY."
[ CHUCKLES ] ME.

04:47.320 --> 04:48.639
[ LAUGHS ]
WHO'S WINNING?

04:48.680 --> 04:50.284
HE'S PLAYING
BY HIMSELF, SIR.

04:50.320 --> 04:53.517
OF COURSE HE IS.
CLASSIC PECK.

04:53.560 --> 04:56.654
"CHUH-LOA PREE-CHAY,"
MY ONE-SHI-IEEYD WONDER.

04:56.690 --> 04:58.920
WHAT, UH, WHAT'S GOING ON THERE?
IS THAT A BUNION?

04:58.960 --> 05:02.225
EW. NO. IT'S JUST -- IT'S --
IT'S -- IT'S A BLISTER.

05:02.260 --> 05:03.090
I'LL --
I'LL PUT MY SHOE ON.

05:03.130 --> 05:04.620
DO YOU EVER HANG OUT
AT JOE'S FISH TANK?

05:04.670 --> 05:07.230
OH, YEAH,
NOT SINCE I WAS 13.

05:07.270 --> 05:09.830
[ Chuckling ]
THAT'S PROBABLY THE LAST TIME
I WORE A SCRUNCHIE.

05:09.870 --> 05:13.101
UH, DOV, UH, HAVE YOU BEEN
TO JOE'S FISH TANK LATELY?

05:13.140 --> 05:14.232
OH, MAN,
I LOVE THAT PLACE.

05:14.280 --> 05:17.374
THEY GOT AN INDOOR ZIPLINE
OVER A SEA OF PLASTIC BALLS.

05:17.410 --> 05:18.377
THAT IS TRUE.

05:18.410 --> 05:19.570
YES, THE ZIPLINE.

05:19.620 --> 05:22.339
ALSO, THEY HAVE
JUST PHAT ACOUSTICS. OKAY?

05:22.390 --> 05:23.982
I AM PLAYING, UM,

05:24.020 --> 05:26.488
I'M PLAYING DRUMS
IN IZZY'S BAND THERE TONIGHT.

05:26.520 --> 05:27.487
YES!
AWESOME.

05:27.520 --> 05:29.488
HERE'S HOPING
NO OVERTIME.

05:29.530 --> 05:30.781
OKAY,
YOU'RE BOTH ON THE LIST.

05:30.830 --> 05:32.388
LIKE, YOU'RE
EACH OTHER'S PLUS-ONE.

05:32.430 --> 05:33.852
SO I NEED
YOUR ENERGY THERE.

05:34.930 --> 05:35.828
FUNNY.

05:37.570 --> 05:38.969
[ SILVERWARE CLINKS ]

05:39.000 --> 05:40.797
H EY, HAN DSOM E.

05:43.210 --> 05:44.108
HEY.

05:44.140 --> 05:46.131
WHAT'S WRONG?

05:46.170 --> 05:48.331
WHAT I TOLD YOU
ABOUT JULIET WARD --

05:48.380 --> 05:49.574
IT'S TRUE. SHE'S I.A.

05:49.610 --> 05:50.838
HOW MANY TIMES
AM I RIGHT?

05:50.880 --> 05:53.110
I MEAN, IS ANYBODY
EVEN KEEPING COUNT ANYMORE?

05:53.150 --> 05:54.219
LISTEN TO ME.

05:54.250 --> 05:55.274
TED MCDONALD SAID

05:55.320 --> 05:57.117
COMMISSIONER SANTANA
WAS CORRUPT.

05:57.150 --> 05:59.084
HE SAID HE HAD EVIDENCE
AGAINST HIM.

05:59.120 --> 06:00.212
MM-HMM.

06:00.260 --> 06:03.127
OKAY? THEN TED MCDONALD DIES,
AND HIS EVIDENCE BLOWS UP.

06:03.160 --> 06:04.422
WHICH IS WHY
JULIET'S HERE.

06:04.460 --> 06:06.325
BECAUSE IF SANTANA
WAS BEHIND THE BOMB,

06:06.360 --> 06:07.918
THEN SOMEONE IN 15
HELPED HIM.

06:07.960 --> 06:08.892
WE'VE BEEN THROUGH THIS.

06:08.930 --> 06:10.591
SANTANA HAS FIGURED OUT
WHY JULIET IS HERE,

06:10.630 --> 06:13.793
AND HE WANTS NOELLE'S REPORT
BY THE END OF THE DAY, 6:00.

06:13.840 --> 06:16.263
WELL, DOES SHE EVEN HAVE
A NAME?

06:16.300 --> 06:18.063
OLIVER SHAW.

06:18.110 --> 06:19.361
[ LAUGHS ]

06:19.410 --> 06:20.434
COME ON.

06:20.480 --> 06:21.629
SAM,
THAT IS RIDICU LOUS.

06:21.680 --> 06:22.977
YEAH, OBVIOUSLY,
IT'S RIDIC--

06:23.010 --> 06:24.978
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT WE THINK, OKAY?

06:25.010 --> 06:27.410
OLIVER'S KEY CARD WAS USED
IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM

06:27.450 --> 06:28.474
THE DAY OF THE BOMBING.

06:28.520 --> 06:30.818
SO? ANYBODY COULD HAVE USED
HIS KEY CARD.

06:30.850 --> 06:32.681
THEN T-THERE'S HIS PROMOTION,
RIGHT?

06:32.720 --> 06:34.312
BEAT COP TO STAFF SERGEANT --
THAT'S A BIG ONE.

06:34.360 --> 06:35.657
HE DIDN'T EVEN WANT
THAT PROMOTION.

06:35.690 --> 06:38.386
ANDY, I'M JUST LOOKING
AT THIS HOW I.A. IS
GONNA LOOK AT IT, OKAY?

06:38.430 --> 06:41.297
IF I WERE THEM,
I WOULD HAVE QUESTIONS.

06:41.330 --> 06:44.390
IF SANTANA IS DIRTY...

06:44.430 --> 06:46.830
AND HE CAN PIN IT
ALL ON OLIVER, HE WILL.

06:46.870 --> 06:49.566
WELL, WHAT ARE WE
SUPPOSED TO DO?

06:49.610 --> 06:52.170
I DON'T KNOW.
WE -- I --

06:52.210 --> 06:54.701
WE FIND OUT WHO HELPED SANTANA,
AND WE CLEAR OLIVER.

06:54.740 --> 06:56.401
WHAT --
BY 6:00 TONIGHT?

06:56.450 --> 06:57.644
[ SIGHS ]

07:02.450 --> 07:05.248
DOV -- DOV WAS WORKING
THE INTELLIGENCE UNIT

07:05.290 --> 07:06.416
BEFORE
JARVIS SHUT THEM DOWN.

07:06.460 --> 07:07.882
I MEAN,
HE'S GOT TO KNOW SOMETHING.

07:07.920 --> 07:10.957
AND I WOULD TRUST HIM
WITH MY LIFE.

07:11.990 --> 07:14.754
OKAY, GO. I'LL CHECK
THE EVIDENCE-ROOM RECORDS.

07:14.800 --> 07:15.892
DOV: TONIGHT?

07:15.930 --> 07:18.069
YES, BY 6:00, OTHERWISE,
SANTANA COULD SEWER OLIVER.

07:18.100 --> 07:18.998
SO, WHAT SHOULD I KNOW?

07:19.030 --> 07:20.634
WE FOUND OUT
WHERE THE BOMB CAME FROM,

07:20.670 --> 07:22.558
BUT IT DIDN'T GO ANYWHERE.
WHERE DID IT COME FROM?

07:22.610 --> 07:24.168
SOME EXPLOSIVES DEALER
NAMED CHRIS KLEM.

07:24.210 --> 07:25.029
WELL, WHERE'S HE AT?

07:25.070 --> 07:27.300
ON A MISSING-PERSONS LIST
IN KITCHENER.

07:27.340 --> 07:29.103
KLEM'S A WIDOWER
AND A SINGLE FATHER.

07:29.140 --> 07:32.075
BOTH HE AND HIS 15-YEAR-OLD
DAUGHTER, AVA, ARE MISSING.

07:32.110 --> 07:32.815
HMM.

07:32.850 --> 07:34.112
DID YOU FOLLOW UP
ON THAT?

07:34.150 --> 07:36.641
I TRIED, BUT JARVIS SHUT US DOWN
ABOUT A MONTH AGO.

07:36.690 --> 07:38.419
UP UNTIL THAT POINT,
THERE'D BEEN NO ACTIVITY

07:38.450 --> 07:39.758
ON HIS CREDIT CARDS
OR BANK ACCOUNTS.

07:39.790 --> 07:41.257
I MEAN,
I COULD CHECK AGAIN TODAY.

07:41.290 --> 07:42.211
YEAH. DO THAT.

07:42.260 --> 07:44.785
OKAY, SAM AND I
ARE GONNA GO TO KITCHENER.

07:44.830 --> 07:46.593
WE'LL TALK
TO THE LOCAL POLICE.

07:46.630 --> 07:49.019
DOV, DO NOT TELL ANYBODY
ABOUT THIS.

07:49.060 --> 07:50.960
OLIVER DOESN'T KNOW.

07:51.000 --> 07:52.865
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

07:52.900 --> 07:55.039
Oliver:
ALL RIGHT, GUYS, LISTEN UP.

07:55.070 --> 07:56.389
FOCUS. LISTEN.

07:56.440 --> 07:58.499
WE HAVE A KID
WHO'S DISAPPEARED FROM HIS HOUSE

07:58.540 --> 07:59.438
OVER IN WESTERLAND COURT.

07:59.470 --> 08:02.473
HIS NAME IS EVAN MALONE.
HE IS 9 YEARS OLD.

08:02.510 --> 08:04.649
THIS IS GOING TO BE
THE FOCUS OF OUR DAY, OKAY?

08:04.680 --> 08:05.908
WE HAVE OFFICERS
ON THE SCENE.

08:05.950 --> 08:08.475
THEY'RE GONNA BE BRINGING PEOPLE
FROM THE NEIGHBORHOOD BACK HERE

08:08.520 --> 08:09.612
FOR QUESTIONING.

08:09.650 --> 08:11.584
HOPEFULLY, SOME OF THOSE FOLKS
ARE GONNA BE WITNESSES

08:11.620 --> 08:13.019
THAT MAY HAVE SEEN EVAN
THIS MORNING.

08:13.060 --> 08:13.719
YES?

08:13.760 --> 08:15.284
HOW LONG
HAS HE BEEN MISSING?

08:15.320 --> 08:16.981
HE'S BEEN GONE
FOR TWO HOURS.

08:17.030 --> 08:17.985
WE TALKING AMBER ALERT?

08:18.030 --> 08:19.827
WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE'RE TALKING ABOUT.

08:19.860 --> 08:22.192
MOORE, WHAT DO WE NEED
FOR AN AMBER ALERT?

08:22.230 --> 08:23.561
EVIDENCE
OF CHILD ABDUCTION.

08:23.600 --> 08:25.329
SO, UH, THE CHILD
MUST BE UNDER 18,

08:25.370 --> 08:26.394
AND WE GOT TO BELIEVE

08:26.430 --> 08:30.207
THAT THEY'RE UNDER THREAT
OF BODILY HARM OR DEATH.

08:30.240 --> 08:33.038
SO, WE WOULD NEED
A DESCRIPTION OF THE SUSPECT

08:33.080 --> 08:34.308
OR AT LEAST A VEHICLE.

08:34.340 --> 08:37.844
AN AMBER ALERT LETS THE WORLD
KNOW THAT A CHILD IS MISSING.

08:37.880 --> 08:40.678
A MISSING-PERSONS REPORT
GETS PUT INTO A FILE.

08:40.720 --> 08:42.711
GO AND FIND ME
WHAT MOORE SAID.

08:42.750 --> 08:47.187
ANY EXTRA INFORMATION WE GET
WILL BE FORWARDED ON TO YOU.

08:47.220 --> 08:48.983
MAKE THIS FAST, FOLKS.

08:49.020 --> 08:50.954
Andy: THEY'VE BEEN MISSING
FOR THREE MONTHS.

08:50.990 --> 08:52.753
Sam: WONDER WHAT STATE
THE HOUSE IS IN.

08:52.800 --> 08:55.553
UH, WELL, KITCHENER P.D.
SAID THEY LEFT IT
THE WAY THEY FOUND IT.

08:55.600 --> 08:56.862
I MEAN,
NOBODY CAN TOUCH IT

08:56.900 --> 08:59.323
UNLESS THEY HAVE
FORMAL DEATH CERTIFICATES, SO...

08:59.370 --> 09:01.531
ANY RELATIVES?

09:01.570 --> 09:02.764
UH, NO CLOSE ONES.

09:02.810 --> 09:04.766
BOTH SETS OF PARENTS
ARE DECEASED.

09:04.810 --> 09:06.368
THERE'S ONE AUNT
IN MILWAUKEE,

09:06.410 --> 09:08.275
BUT SHE HASN'T HEARD FROM HIM
IN YEARS.

09:08.310 --> 09:09.504
MISSING PERSONS --

09:09.540 --> 09:11.747
LOW PRIORITY
UNLESS SOMEBODY'S MAKING NOISE.

09:11.780 --> 09:13.714
WELL,
LET'S MAKE SOME NOISE.

09:16.620 --> 09:18.212
IT'S RIGHT HERE.

09:20.320 --> 09:22.857
THE HOUSE CERTAINLY LOOKS LIKE
YOU'D EXPECT IT TO.

09:22.890 --> 09:23.754
WELL...

09:23.790 --> 09:24.984
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

09:25.030 --> 09:26.895
I'VE NOTICED, UH...
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:26.930 --> 09:29.125
YOU HAVEN'T BEEN WEARING
YOUR RING.

09:29.160 --> 09:30.229
OH, YEAH.

09:30.270 --> 09:32.864
WELL, I-I KIND OF DEVELOPED,
UH, AN ALLERGIC REACTION.

09:32.900 --> 09:33.867
OH.

09:33.900 --> 09:35.765
UM, BUT THERE'S ACTUALLY
A SPRAY THAT I CAN GET

09:35.800 --> 09:37.108
THAT WILL MAKE IT --

09:37.140 --> 09:38.630
SHE'S HERE.

09:40.580 --> 09:41.877
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

09:44.380 --> 09:45.278
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

09:45.310 --> 09:46.402
HI.

09:46.450 --> 09:47.747
Lorraine:
HI, THERE. McNALLY?
YES.

09:47.780 --> 09:48.872
SWAREK, HI.
DETECTIVE NORMAN.

09:48.920 --> 09:50.979
HEY, THANKS FOR COMING
TO MEET US ON SUCH SHORT NOTICE.

09:51.020 --> 09:52.214
WE'VE, UH,
WE'VE SEEN THE FILE,

09:52.250 --> 09:54.218
BUT MAYBE YOU COULD FILL US IN
FROM YOUR END?

09:54.260 --> 09:55.284
YEAH, FOR SURE.

09:55.320 --> 09:57.686
UH, THE NEIGHBORS FOUND THE DOG
LOCKED OUTSIDE --

09:57.730 --> 09:59.618
NO FOOD, NO WATER --
SO THEY CALLED US.

09:59.660 --> 10:01.548
SCHOOL HADN'T SEEN AVA
FOR A COUPLE OF DAYS,

10:01.600 --> 10:02.760
SO WE STARTED
LOOKING FOR HER.

10:02.800 --> 10:04.427
WHERE'S THE DOG NOW?
OH, THE NEIGHBOR TOOK IT.

10:04.470 --> 10:07.860
I WOULD HAVE TOOK IT MYSELF,
EXCEPT I ALREADY GOT A DOG.

10:16.680 --> 10:18.477
IT'S WEIRD, RIGHT?

10:18.510 --> 10:20.740
THEY DISAPPEARED
INTO THIN AIR.

10:22.380 --> 10:24.712
IF I WERE THE RELIGIOUS TYPE,
I'D SWEAR THEY WERE RAPTURED.

10:31.930 --> 10:33.852
DID YOU SPEAK
WITH ANYONE, UH,

10:33.900 --> 10:36.460
THAT MENTIONED
MAYBE HE WAS TAKING A TRIP?

10:36.500 --> 10:38.593
NOT THAT I HEARD.

10:38.630 --> 10:40.894
THERE WAS NOTHING UNUSUAL
WITH THIS GUY.

10:40.940 --> 10:43.306
HE WAS NORMAL,
WELL-LIKED.

10:43.340 --> 10:45.661
HIS MORTGAGE WAS PAID OFF.
HE WASN'T EVEN IN DEBT.

10:45.710 --> 10:47.507
DETECTIVE, HAVE YOU
AND THE LOCAL POLICE

10:47.540 --> 10:49.337
REALLY TRIED
TO FIND THIS FAMILY?

10:49.380 --> 10:50.847
W-WHAT'S BEEN
YOUR FOLLOW-U P?

10:50.880 --> 10:53.644
YOU KNOW, WE LOOKED FOR THEM.
THEY'RE GONE.

10:54.950 --> 10:57.589
WHO KNOWS? MAYBE
THEY DIDN'T LIKE THE CLIMATE.

10:57.620 --> 10:58.939
YOU DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS ODD

10:58.990 --> 11:00.787
THEY LEFT THEIR PASSPORTS
BEHIND?

11:00.820 --> 11:04.381
SOMETIMES
PEOPLE JUST UP AND LEAVE.

11:04.430 --> 11:08.127
YOU KNOW, THEY JOIN A CULT,
THEY DEVELOP A MENTAL ILLNESS,

11:08.160 --> 11:09.092
THEY GET ALZHEIMER'S

11:09.130 --> 11:10.995
AND, YOU KNOW,
WANDER INTO THE OBLIVION.

11:11.030 --> 11:12.998
OKAY, WELL,
CHRIS KLEM IS 39 YEARS OLD.

11:13.040 --> 11:15.235
I HIGHLY DOUBT
THAT HE DEVELOPED ALZHEIMER'S.

11:15.270 --> 11:18.239
BUT I GUESS IT IS PLAUSIBLE THAT
THEY WERE ABDUCTED BY ALIENS.

11:18.270 --> 11:21.706
HEY, DON'T THINK WE DIDN'T BANDY
THAT ONE AROUND THE PRECINCT.

11:23.710 --> 11:27.214
SO, UH...YOU GUYS
GOT EVERYTHING YOU NEED?

11:27.250 --> 11:28.444
ARE YOU IN A HURRY?

11:28.480 --> 11:32.211
OH, YOU'RE NOT IN A HURRY?
DOWN IN THE BIG CITY?

11:34.790 --> 11:37.281
YOU KNOW WHAT?
I'LL JUST -- I'LL WAIT OUTSIDE.

11:46.330 --> 11:47.331
WHAT ARE YOU THINKING?

11:47.370 --> 11:50.134
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
WHAT ARE WE LOOKING FOR?

11:50.170 --> 11:52.502
FORENSICS WENT OVER
THIS PLACE, RIGHT?

11:52.540 --> 11:53.677
NO SIGN OF A STRUGGLE.

11:53.710 --> 11:55.473
YOU THINK THEY WERE PAID
TO DISAPPEAR?

11:55.510 --> 11:58.172
NEW NAMES, NEW I.D.s,

11:58.210 --> 12:00.178
DISAPPEARED
INTO CHILEAN PATAGONIA.

12:00.220 --> 12:01.778
OKAY, LET'S SAY
THEY HAD A CHOICE. RIGHT?

12:01.820 --> 12:03.447
THEY WOULD PROBABLY
TAKE SOME STUFF WITH THEM.

12:03.490 --> 12:04.479
WHAT KIND OF STUFF?

12:04.520 --> 12:06.010
LIKE SENTIMENTAL THINGS,
THINGS THAT MATTER TO THEM

12:06.050 --> 12:08.587
THAT MAYBE THEY THOUGHT
WE WOULD NEVER NOTICE.

12:08.620 --> 12:09.416
SMALL STUFF.

12:09.460 --> 12:10.427
IT WOULDN'T HURT TO LOOK,
YOU KNOW,

12:10.460 --> 12:13.258
KIND OF SEE IF THEY WERE
FORCED TO LEAVE OR NOT.

12:13.300 --> 12:16.258
ALL RIGHT. I'LL START UPSTAIRS.
IT'S A GOOD IDEA.

12:18.800 --> 12:21.769
EVAN WAS WEARING A RED HOODIE
AND PAJAMA PANTS.

12:21.800 --> 12:23.700
HE WAS READING
ONE OF HIS FANTASY BOOKS

12:23.740 --> 12:25.037
OUTSIDE IN THE YARD.

12:25.070 --> 12:27.868
HE'S QUIET. HE DOESN'T HAVE
A LOT OF FRIENDS.

12:29.540 --> 12:31.007
WHERE'S EVAN'S FATHER?

12:31.050 --> 12:33.109
I CALLED.
I HAVEN'T HEARD BACK.

12:33.150 --> 12:35.311
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF A DIVORCE.

12:35.350 --> 12:37.614
WHY ISN'T THERE
AN AMBER ALERT YET?

12:37.650 --> 12:39.379
I PROMISE YOU --
WE'RE WORKING ON THAT.

12:39.420 --> 12:40.580
OKAY.

12:40.620 --> 12:43.327
BUT WHOEVER TOOK EVAN COULD BE
CROSSING THE BORDER RIGHT NOW.

12:43.360 --> 12:45.521
AND AN AMBER ALERT
IS NOT GONNA HELP US.

12:45.560 --> 12:46.652
MRS. MALONE,

12:46.690 --> 12:49.625
WE WOULDN'T KNOW WHAT MODEL
OR MAKE OF CAR TO STOP.

12:49.660 --> 12:52.458
BEFORE WE PROCEED, WE NEED
TO KNOW WHAT WE'RE LOOKING FOR.

12:52.500 --> 12:54.092
S-SO THAT'S
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

12:54.140 --> 12:56.267
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT WE'RE DOING. OKAY?

12:56.300 --> 12:58.905
EVERYONE HERE
IS LOOKING FOR YOUR SON.

12:58.940 --> 13:00.305
OKAY.
OKAY.

13:00.340 --> 13:01.409
Traci: STAFF.

13:03.410 --> 13:05.401
YOU'LL HAVE TO
EXCUSE ME.

13:05.450 --> 13:06.576
YEAH?

13:06.610 --> 13:09.738
OKAY, SO, NICK SPOKE TO
A NEIGHBOR NAMED GARY FULHAM.

13:09.780 --> 13:10.747
HE WAS GARDENING.

13:10.790 --> 13:13.486
HE SAW THE BOY TALKING
TO THAT GUY -- RHYS GRAY.

13:13.520 --> 13:15.579
HE THEN WENT FOR A DRIVE-THROUGH
BREAKFAST SANDWICH.

13:15.620 --> 13:16.780
WHEN HE CAME BACK,
THEY WERE BOTH GONE.

13:16.830 --> 13:18.229
OKAY, RUN THOSE NAMES.
ALREADY ON IT.

13:18.260 --> 13:20.353
CHLOE'S CHECKING THE NAMES
OF EVERYONE WHO WALKS IN HERE.
OKAY. THANKS.

13:20.400 --> 13:22.550
Gail: HOW LONG HAVE YOU LIVED
ON WESTERLAND COURT?

13:22.600 --> 13:24.795
14 YEARS
THIS COMING WINTER.

13:24.830 --> 13:26.491
SO, DID YOU SEE THE BOY
THIS MORNING?

13:26.530 --> 13:29.363
YEAH. EVAN CAME OVER
TO WATCH ME FROM NEXT DOOR.

13:29.400 --> 13:32.631
I'D JUST RESCUED THIS AMAZING
SHABBY-CHIC HEADBOARD,

13:32.670 --> 13:33.978
AND I WAS REPAINTING IT.

13:34.010 --> 13:36.069
HIGH-GLOSS ORANGE?

13:36.110 --> 13:38.601
YOU CAN NEVER GO WRONG
WITH HIGH-GLOSS ORANGE.

13:38.650 --> 13:40.971
WHAT TIME
DID YOU TALK TO EVAN?

13:41.020 --> 13:43.238
AROUND, UH, 8:00 AM.

13:43.290 --> 13:46.043
UM [CHUCKLES] HE WAS
YAKKING AWAY TO HIMSELF,

13:46.090 --> 13:48.388
AND I ASKED HIM
WHO HE WAS TALKING TO,

13:48.420 --> 13:50.888
AND HE LOOKED AT ME
LIKE I WAS CRAZY.

13:50.930 --> 13:52.329
AND I WAS LIKE,

13:52.360 --> 13:54.658
"UH, YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO'S TALKING TO YOURSELF."

13:54.700 --> 13:55.519
OH.

13:55.560 --> 13:59.519
THAT'S NOT FUNNY
'CAUSE HE'S MISSING.

13:59.570 --> 14:01.037
HOW LONG
WAS EVAN WITH YOU?

14:01.070 --> 14:02.697
JUST A FEW MINUTES.

14:02.740 --> 14:04.264
I WENT IN
TO GET MORE COFFEE,

14:04.310 --> 14:06.198
AND WHEN I CAME BACK,
HE WAS GONE,

14:06.240 --> 14:08.128
SO I FIGURED
HE'D GONE HOME.

14:08.180 --> 14:09.101
[ SIGHS ]

14:09.140 --> 14:10.778
I HOPE HE'S OKAY.
I MEAN, HE'S A SWEET KID.

14:10.810 --> 14:11.799
Chloe: OFFICER PECK?

14:11.850 --> 14:13.317
WHAT'S UP?

14:13.350 --> 14:16.274
HI. CAN I HAVE A WORD,
PLEASE?

14:16.320 --> 14:17.514
EXCUSE ME.

14:20.820 --> 14:23.084
UH, SO, YOUR GUY'S
IN THE SYSTEM.

14:23.130 --> 14:25.928
RHYS GRAY IS
A REGISTERED SEX OFFENDER.

14:30.030 --> 14:31.861
ALL RIGHT, RHYS,
THIS IS DETECTIVE NASH.

14:31.900 --> 14:33.788
SHE'S JUST GONNA ASK YOU
A FEW QUESTIONS.

14:33.840 --> 14:34.795
OKAY,
BUT [CLEARS THROAT]

14:34.840 --> 14:36.831
I VOLUNTEERED TO COME IN
AND TALK TO YOU,

14:36.870 --> 14:39.361
SO WHY AM I NOW
TALKING TO A DETECTIVE?

14:39.410 --> 14:41.674
MR. GRAY,
IT'S COME TO OUR ATTENTION

14:41.710 --> 14:43.177
THAT YOU ARE
A REGISTERED --

14:43.210 --> 14:45.906
NO. NO, I'M NOT.
I'M -- I'M NOT A SEX OFFENDER.

14:45.950 --> 14:49.818
BUT OUR SYSTEM IDENTIFIED
A RHYS GRAY

14:49.850 --> 14:51.579
OF 102 WESTERLAND COURT
AS A SEX OFFENDER.

14:51.620 --> 14:52.689
THAT'S NOT YOU?

14:52.720 --> 14:54.551
[ SIGHS ]

14:54.590 --> 14:57.127
IT WAS 20 YEARS AGO.

14:57.160 --> 15:00.095
THE COPS CAUGHT ME IN A CAR
WITH A GUY WHO SAID HE WAS 18.

15:00.130 --> 15:02.348
HE WAS ACTUALLY 17.

15:02.400 --> 15:03.594
BUT I WAS 25,

15:03.630 --> 15:06.121
SO THEY CHARGED ME
WITH SEXUAL ABUSE OF A MINOR.

15:06.170 --> 15:07.660
AND NOW
YOU HAVE A RECORD.

15:07.700 --> 15:08.928
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE.

15:08.970 --> 15:10.062
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:10.110 --> 15:11.964
AND, YOU KNOW,
IF IT HAD BEEN STRAIGHT SEX,

15:12.010 --> 15:13.409
I WOULDN'T EVEN
HAVE BEEN CHARGED.

15:13.440 --> 15:16.329
AGE OF CONSENT FOR GAY SEX,
AT THE TIME, WAS 18,

15:16.380 --> 15:18.701
BUT F-FOR STRAIGHT SEX,
IT WAS 16.

15:18.750 --> 15:20.115
I-IT WAS DISCRIMINATION.

15:20.150 --> 15:22.618
DO WE HAVE YOUR PERMISSION
TO SEARCH YOUR HOUSE?

15:22.650 --> 15:24.515
I HAD NOTHING
TO DO WITH THIS.

15:24.550 --> 15:25.448
WHAT IF I SAY NO?

15:25.490 --> 15:27.958
THEN WE'LL TAKE THE TIME
TO GET A WARRANT,

15:27.990 --> 15:30.379
BUT THIS IS
A MISSING CHILD, MR. GRAY.

15:30.430 --> 15:31.351
EVERY SECOND COUNTS.

15:31.390 --> 15:34.257
FINE. DO IT. GO.
JUST SEARCH AWAY.

15:36.000 --> 15:37.092
[ SCOFFS ]

15:37.130 --> 15:38.859
[Voice breaking ]
IT WAS ONE MOMENT,

15:38.900 --> 15:43.064
AND I WILL NEVER
ESCAPE IT.

15:48.710 --> 15:49.802
[ SIGHS ]

15:49.840 --> 15:52.240
THERE'S A FULL JEWELRY BOX
UPSTAIRS, AMONG OTHER THINGS.

15:52.280 --> 15:54.316
THEY DIDN'T TAKE
ANY OF THAT STUFF.

15:54.350 --> 15:55.374
MM.

15:55.420 --> 15:59.140
GOT A BABY BOOK HERE --
FIRST TEETH, BABY HAIR,

15:59.190 --> 16:01.055
GOT A BUNCH OF PICTURES.

16:01.090 --> 16:03.581
THIS IS AN URN.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.029
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

16:05.060 --> 16:06.857
I DON'T THINK
THIS FAMILY LEFT WILLINGLY.

16:06.890 --> 16:08.721
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

16:08.760 --> 16:11.695
HEY, DOV.
YOU FIND ANYTHING?

16:11.730 --> 16:14.164
YEAH, I'M HITTING WALLS HERE.
I NEED HIGHER CLEARANCE.

16:14.200 --> 16:15.337
WELL, WHERE'S TRACI AT?

16:15.370 --> 16:16.439
Missing kid.

16:16.470 --> 16:18.665
OLIVER'S RUNNING IT, THOUGH.
MAYBE I CAN TALK TO HER.

16:18.710 --> 16:20.302
[ SIGHS ] OKAY.

16:20.340 --> 16:23.173
PULL HER INTO THIS.
NOBODY ELSE, ALL RIGHT?

16:23.210 --> 16:24.575
OKAY.

16:25.910 --> 16:27.946
[ Singsong voice ]
HELLO!

16:27.980 --> 16:28.947
HI. [ CHUCKLES ]

16:28.980 --> 16:30.208
Sam: HI.
CAN WE HELP YOU?

16:30.250 --> 16:34.789
UH, YEAH, I'M, UH, ERIN JESSO,
NOSEY NEIGHBOR

16:34.820 --> 16:37.380
AND, UH,
TEMPORARY KEEPER OF TARZAN.

16:37.430 --> 16:39.455
WHAT -- W-WHO --
WHAT IS THAT?

16:41.530 --> 16:42.497
TARZAN KLEM.

16:42.530 --> 16:43.462
OKAY.
OH.

16:43.500 --> 16:45.388
TRUST ME,
IT WOULDN'T BE MY FIRST CHOICE.

16:45.430 --> 16:46.499
[ LAUGHS ]

16:46.530 --> 16:48.737
I'M SINGLE AND 45,
AND PEOPLE THINK I'M ODD ENOUGH

16:48.770 --> 16:51.705
WITHOUT ME RUNNING AROUND
THE PARK YELLING, "TARZAN!"

16:51.740 --> 16:53.731
UM...D--

16:53.780 --> 16:56.669
DID MR. KLEM SAY ANYTHING TO YOU
ABOUT, UH, LEAVING TOWN?

16:56.710 --> 16:57.608
NO.

16:57.650 --> 17:01.416
LIKE I TOLD DETECTIVE NORMAN
MONTHS AGO,

17:01.450 --> 17:04.385
HE WOULD HAVE ASKED ME TO WATER
THE PLANTS, WALK THE DOG.

17:04.420 --> 17:06.388
I WAS REALLY CLOSE
WITH HIS WIFE.

17:06.420 --> 17:08.718
RIGHT.
WHEN DID SHE PASS AWAY?

17:08.760 --> 17:10.250
UM, FOUR YEARS AGO.

17:10.290 --> 17:12.383
SUSAN REALLY LIKED MUSIC,

17:12.430 --> 17:16.252
SO CHRIS HAD HER RADIO
CONVERTED INTO AN URN.

17:16.300 --> 17:19.019
DID YOU NOTICE ANY ODD BEHAVIOR
BETWEEN EITHER OF THEM

17:19.070 --> 17:20.094
THE LAST FEW MONTHS?

17:20.140 --> 17:22.734
YEAH,
THERE WAS ONE INCIDENT.

17:22.770 --> 17:25.705
UH, ONE NIGHT,
A COP CAR PULLED UP OUT FRONT,

17:25.740 --> 17:28.538
AND AVA WAS INSIDE.

17:28.580 --> 17:29.535
HER DAD WENT OUT,

17:29.580 --> 17:32.140
AND THERE WAS A BIG BLOWUP
ON THE FRONT LAWN.

17:32.180 --> 17:34.011
SHE WAS GOING THROUGH
A DIFFICULT STAGE?

17:34.050 --> 17:36.041
THE FIGHT WASN'T
BETWEEN CHRIS AND AVA.

17:36.080 --> 17:37.741
IT WAS
BETWEEN CHRIS AND THE COP.

17:37.790 --> 17:40.281
I-I TALKED TO DETECTIVE NORMAN
ABOUT IT, BUT SHE SAID

17:40.320 --> 17:42.857
IT DIDN'T HAVE ANYTHING TO DO
WITH THE DISAPPEARANCE.

17:42.890 --> 17:44.323
HOW WOULD SHE KNOW THAT?

17:44.360 --> 17:47.056
SHE WAS THE COP
THAT BROUGHT AVA HOME.

17:48.330 --> 17:50.161
UH, WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT EVAN MALONE,

17:50.200 --> 17:51.428
THE BOY
FROM ACROSS THE STREET?

17:51.470 --> 17:53.529
WELL,
I SAW HIM THIS MORNING.

17:53.570 --> 17:57.461
I FOUND A NEON BAR SIGN
DOWN THE ROAD

17:57.510 --> 18:00.138
PRACTICALLY BRAND-NEW --
PERFECT FOR MY MAN CAVE.

18:00.180 --> 18:02.603
EVAN WAS THERE
WHEN I BROUGHT IT HOME.

18:02.640 --> 18:03.538
HE LOOKED FINE TO ME.

18:03.580 --> 18:05.901
DO YOU KNOW
THE BOY'S PARENTS?

18:05.950 --> 18:06.678
DIVORCED.

18:06.710 --> 18:08.519
THEY SEEMED HAPPY
AT FIRST --

18:08.550 --> 18:11.678
PUBLIC DISPLAYS OF AFFECT ION
AT THE FIVE-AND-DIME

18:11.720 --> 18:12.789
AND ALL THAT.

18:12.820 --> 18:13.889
NO MYSTERY THERE.

18:13.920 --> 18:15.148
BUT...

18:15.190 --> 18:17.226
WHY WAS THE EX-HUSBAND

18:17.260 --> 18:20.149
CREEPING AROUND HER HOUSE
THIS MORNING?

18:20.200 --> 18:22.225
THAT'S A MYSTERY.

18:24.970 --> 18:26.699
WHAT IS A REGISTERED
SEX OFFENDER DOING

18:26.730 --> 18:29.198
LIVING IN A NEIGHBORHOOD
THAT'S FULL OF CHILDREN?

18:29.240 --> 18:30.969
WELL, MS. MALONE,
THAT'S THE LAW --

18:31.010 --> 18:32.068
AT LEAST FOR RIGHT NOW.

18:32.110 --> 18:33.737
YOU KNOW,
IT'S -- IT'S NOT MANDATORY

18:33.780 --> 18:36.101
FOR SEX OFFENDERS TO REGISTER
WHERE THEY'RE LIVING.

18:36.140 --> 18:37.141
ONCE THEY DO THEIR TIME,

18:37.180 --> 18:38.704
THEY CAN LIVE
WHEREVER THEY'D LIKE.

18:38.750 --> 18:41.173
IF EVAN HAD ANY DEALINGS
WITH HIM, I DIDN'T SEE IT.

18:42.780 --> 18:43.883
THAT DOESN'T
MEAN MUCH.

18:43.920 --> 18:45.387
PETER, PLEASE DON'T.

18:45.420 --> 18:47.479
THIS IS EVAN'S FATHER,
PETER MALONE.

18:47.520 --> 18:48.555
FINE.

18:48.590 --> 18:50.524
WHY DON'T YOU TWO, UH,
HAVE A SEAT IN THE LOUNGE?

18:50.560 --> 18:53.051
THERE'S COFFEE IN THERE.
WE'LL -- WE'LL KEEP YOU POSTED.

18:53.090 --> 18:54.421
PROMISE.

18:55.900 --> 18:58.118
OKAY. YOU THINK
RHYS IS OUR GUY?

18:58.170 --> 18:59.467
HE HAD AN EXPLANATION.

18:59.500 --> 19:00.592
I...

19:00.640 --> 19:02.130
TRACE, I DON'T KNOW.
I DON'T KNOW.

19:02.170 --> 19:03.364
MAYBE HE'S PLAYING US.

19:03.410 --> 19:05.162
MAYBE HE CAME IN 'CAUSE HE WANTS
TO KNOW WHAT WE KNOW.

19:05.210 --> 19:06.905
WELL, WE CAN'T HOLD HIM
ONCE WE CLEAR HIS HOUSE.

19:06.940 --> 19:08.271
YES, I KNOW THAT.

19:08.310 --> 19:10.244
MAYBE HE'S GOT EVAN
STASHED SOMEWHERE ELSE,
AT A DIFFERENT LOCATION.

19:10.280 --> 19:11.702
YOU KNOW,
IF WE HAVE AN AMBER ALERT,

19:11.750 --> 19:14.218
AT LEAST THEN WE CAN KEEP
TABS ON HIM AND WE CAN
KEEP LOOKING FOR THE KID.

19:14.250 --> 19:16.810
EVAN'S UNDER 18,
BUT RIGHT NOW

19:16.850 --> 19:18.989
WE HAVE NO EVIDENCE
THAT HE'S BEEN KIDNAPPED.

19:19.020 --> 19:20.089
EXCEPT WE HAVE A WITNESS

19:20.120 --> 19:22.452
WHO SAW THAT KID TALKING
TO A REGISTERED SEX OFFENDER.

19:22.490 --> 19:24.424
A REGISTERED SEX OFFENDER
WHO IS COOPERATING.

19:24.460 --> 19:27.156
THAT DOESN'T MATTER TO ME.
I THINK IT'S WORTH A SHOT.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.760
UH, I AM GOING TO, UH,
I'M GONNA CALL MY INSPECTOR,

19:29.800 --> 19:32.826
AND I'M GONNA GET HIM TO WORK ON
AN AMBER ALERT FOR EVAN.

19:32.870 --> 19:34.030
OH, THANK GOD.

19:34.070 --> 19:36.595
STAFF?
UH, CAN I HAVE A WORD?

19:36.640 --> 19:37.402
YEAH.

19:37.440 --> 19:39.533
IS THIS
ABOUT MY SON?

19:39.570 --> 19:42.573
IF THIS IS ABOUT EVAN,
I WANT TO KNOW -- NOW.

19:42.610 --> 19:44.601
OKAY.

19:46.350 --> 19:48.215
ALL RIGHT, I HAVE A WITNESS
THAT PLACES MR. MALONE

19:48.250 --> 19:49.569
AT HIS EX-WIFE'S HOUSE
THIS MORNING,

19:49.620 --> 19:51.417
RIGHT AROUND THE TIME
OF EVAN'S DISAPPEARANCE.

19:51.450 --> 19:53.281
YOU WERE AT THE HOUSE?

19:53.320 --> 19:55.311
I WANTED THE GARDEN HOSE.
I DIDN'T WANT TO BOTHER YOU.

19:55.360 --> 19:57.521
MAYBE WE SHOULD SPEAK TO YOU
SEPARATELY, MR. MALONE.

19:57.560 --> 20:00.051
Y-YOU GUYS THINK
I KIDNAPPED MY OWN KID?

20:00.090 --> 20:01.626
HE DIDN'T.

20:01.660 --> 20:03.992
PETER ISN'T INTERESTED
IN SHARING CUSTODY.

20:04.030 --> 20:05.361
HE'S NEVER EVEN
HAD HIM OVERNIGHT.

20:05.400 --> 20:07.698
HOW CAN I LOOK AFTER SOMEONE
WHO WON'T CONNECT WITH ME?

20:07.740 --> 20:08.764
PETER.

20:08.800 --> 20:10.836
EXCUSE ME, FOLKS.
I-I'M NOT QUITE FOLLOWING HERE.

20:10.870 --> 20:13.907
WHY IS YOUR SON
NOT CONNECTING WITH YOU, SIR?

20:13.940 --> 20:15.635
[ SIGHS ]

20:15.680 --> 20:17.841
EVAN'S ON
THE AUTISM SPECTRUM.

20:17.880 --> 20:19.177
I SEE.
BARELY.

20:19.210 --> 20:20.677
I DIDN'T WANT
TO SAY ANYTHING.

20:20.720 --> 20:22.915
SHANNON THINKS
POLICE WON'T ISSUE AMBER ALERTS

20:22.950 --> 20:24.349
FOR CHILDREN WITH AUTISM.

20:24.390 --> 20:27.018
WE WILL.
IF THE CRITERIA IS MET, WE WILL.

20:27.050 --> 20:28.950
PARENTS TALK.

20:28.990 --> 20:30.548
I'VE HEARD
THAT LAW ENFORCEMENT

20:30.590 --> 20:32.729
TENDS TO DISMISS
CHILDREN ON THE SPECTRUM

20:32.760 --> 20:35.024
AS WANDERERS,
LIKE THEY'RE ALL THE SAME.

20:35.060 --> 20:37.893
IS EVAN --
IS HE A WANDERER?

20:42.070 --> 20:43.901
YES.

20:43.940 --> 20:46.033
BUT NOT TODAY.

20:46.070 --> 20:48.675
TODAY, HE'S SOMEWHERE.

20:48.710 --> 20:49.574
AND HE'S SCARED.

20:49.610 --> 20:51.407
AND HE WANTS US
TO COME AND GET HIM NOW,

20:51.450 --> 20:53.771
BUT WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE TO LOOK.

20:53.820 --> 20:55.947
PLEASE HELP US.

20:55.980 --> 20:57.811
EXCUSE ME.

21:00.390 --> 21:01.812
YOU CALLING JARVIS?

21:01.860 --> 21:03.259
IAM.

21:03.290 --> 21:06.487
BUT I THINK I KNOW
WHAT THE ANSWER'S GONNA BE.

21:09.900 --> 21:11.663
YOU SAID YOU NEVER MET
CHRIS KLEM. ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

21:11.700 --> 21:13.895
NO. I SAID
I NEVER KNEW HIM PERSONALLY.

21:13.940 --> 21:15.134
WHAT ABOUT AVA?

21:15.170 --> 21:16.137
SAME.

21:16.170 --> 21:17.660
YOU DIDN'T THINK
IT WAS IMPORTANT TO MENTION

21:17.710 --> 21:19.564
THAT YOU BROUGHT AVA HOME
IN A SQUAD CAR

21:19.610 --> 21:22.204
AND HAD A CONFRONTATION ON
THE FRONT LAWN WITH HER FATHER?

21:22.240 --> 21:23.468
I RECEIVED INFORMATION

21:23.510 --> 21:26.172
STATING THAT AVA MAY HAVE DRUGS
ON HER PERSON,

21:26.210 --> 21:27.279
SO I PICKED HER UP.

21:27.320 --> 21:28.719
INFORMATION FROM WHOM?

21:28.750 --> 21:30.911
SOMEBODY HIGHER UP IN THE BLUES
THAN YOU.

21:30.950 --> 21:32.178
OOH!

21:32.220 --> 21:34.484
AND DID SHE
HAVE DRUGS ON HER?

21:34.520 --> 21:35.953
NO.

21:37.120 --> 21:38.985
BY THE TIME I REACHED HER,
SHE MUST HAVE STASHED THEM.

21:39.030 --> 21:40.657
WHO'D YOU SPEAK TO?

21:40.700 --> 21:42.327
THAT CALL
WAS CONFIDENTIAL.

21:42.360 --> 21:43.327
WELL, DID THIS HIGHER-UP
ALSO TELL YOU

21:43.370 --> 21:46.066
NOT TO LOOK FOR THEM
AFTER THEY DISAPPEARED?

21:47.670 --> 21:49.968
YOU DIDN'T THINK
THAT WAS STRANGE?

21:50.000 --> 21:51.001
LISTEN, GUYS,

21:51.040 --> 21:53.099
I HAVE A HUGE RESPECT
FOR THE CITY POLICE FORCE.

21:53.140 --> 21:55.404
ANYTHING THAT I CAN DO
TO HELP YOU GUYS ON THIS END,

21:55.440 --> 21:56.532
I'M HAPPY TO ASSIST,
OKAY?

21:56.580 --> 21:57.501
NO QUESTIONS ASKED.

21:57.550 --> 21:59.575
NO, UH, THANK YOU.
YOU'VE BEEN VERY HELPFUL.

21:59.610 --> 22:01.339
APPRECIATE IT, DETECTIVE.
THANK YOU.

22:01.380 --> 22:02.813
OKAY.
YEP.
THANKS.

22:06.250 --> 22:07.808
Andy: WHAT WAS THAT?

22:07.860 --> 22:09.350
I MESSED IT UP.

22:09.390 --> 22:10.948
I MESSED THIS UP.

22:10.990 --> 22:11.684
HOW?

22:11.730 --> 22:12.879
I MESSED
THIS WHOLE THING UP.

22:12.930 --> 22:14.488
I-I SHOULD HAVE
BEEN ON THIS FASTER.

22:14.530 --> 22:16.157
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?
YOU PUT I.A. ON IT.

22:16.200 --> 22:19.499
AND NOW MY BEST FRIEND IS
THE GUY ON THEIR SUSPECT LIST.

22:19.530 --> 22:20.997
NOBODY IS GONNA BELIEVE
THAT OLIVER'S CORRUPT.

22:21.040 --> 22:22.735
WE DON'T --
OKAY?
NO, IT'S NOT EVEN POSSIBLE.

22:22.770 --> 22:24.738
WE DON'T KNOW WHAT
THEY'RE GONNA BELIEVE, OKAY?

22:24.770 --> 22:26.738
IT HAPPENS TO COPS
YOU'D NEVER EXPECT.

22:26.770 --> 22:29.273
SOMEBODY HANDS YOU YOUR
NEXT THREE MORTGAGE PAYMENTS

22:29.310 --> 22:31.141
TO LET SOMEONE
SLIP OUT OF A POT BUST,

22:31.180 --> 22:33.546
ANOTHER COUPLE OF
MORTGAGE PAYMENTS FOR
A LITTLE INFORMATION.

22:33.580 --> 22:35.013
NEXT THING YOU KNOW,
THEY OWN YOU.

22:35.050 --> 22:37.268
YOU'RE DOING THINGS
YOU NEVER THOUGHT YOU WOULD

22:37.320 --> 22:39.288
JUST TO SAVE YOURSELF,
YOUR JOB, YOUR FAMILY.

22:39.320 --> 22:42.187
YEAH, WELL, NOT OLIVER.

22:42.220 --> 22:43.482
[ SIGHS ]

22:44.860 --> 22:47.727
IZZY GOT INTO A LITTLE TROUBLE
A WHILE BACK.

22:47.760 --> 22:50.729
SHE GOT CAUGHT
WITH SOME ECSTASY ON HER.

22:50.770 --> 22:54.729
SANTANA OFFERED
TO WIPE IT FROM THE SYSTEM.

22:54.770 --> 22:57.432
HE WAS OLIVER'S T.O.
BEFORE, UH, YOUR DAD.

22:57.470 --> 22:59.563
I KNOW THAT.

23:00.610 --> 23:03.443
OLIVER ASKED ME
WHETHER OR NOT HE SHOULD ACCEPT.

23:03.480 --> 23:05.573
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

23:05.610 --> 23:07.771
I SAID IF HE DID,
TO KEEP IT BETWEEN US.

23:07.820 --> 23:10.482
AND I KNOW I SHOULD HAVE
TOLD HIM NOT TO DO IT.

23:10.520 --> 23:12.044
AND NOW IT'LL MAKE HIM
LOOK EVEN MORE GUILTY.

23:12.090 --> 23:14.058
YEAH, HE LOOKS LIKE
THE PERFECT SCAPEGOAT NOW.

23:14.090 --> 23:16.479
AND WE DON'T HAVE CHRIS KLEM
TO TELL US IT WASN'T HIM.

23:24.070 --> 23:26.766
ALL RIGHT, WE JUST FINISHED
SEARCHING RHYS' HOUSE.

23:26.800 --> 23:29.496
NO KID, NO SECRET COMPARTMENT,
NO WEIRD SEARCHES ONLINE.

23:29.540 --> 23:31.235
ALL RIGHT,
THAT MEANS THAT RHYS GRAY --

23:31.270 --> 23:32.669
WE GOT TO LET HIM
WALK OUT OF HERE,

23:32.710 --> 23:34.302
AND WE HAVE
NO AMBER ALERT.

23:34.340 --> 23:37.901
WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO FIND THIS
KID WITH APB AND BOLOS, OKAY?

23:37.950 --> 23:40.748
THERE WAS NOTHING UNUSUAL
AT THAT HOUSE?

23:40.780 --> 23:43.419
NOTHING, EXCEPT THERE WAS
ORANGE PAINT ALL OVER THE PORCH.

23:43.450 --> 23:45.486
HE WAS PAINTING
BEFORE HE GOT HERE.

23:45.520 --> 23:48.159
HE WAS STOKED ABOUT
FINDING SOME HEADBOARD IN
THE GARBAGE THIS MORNING.

23:48.190 --> 23:49.088
WELL, THAT'S WEIRD.

23:49.120 --> 23:50.985
I TALKED TO A GUY
WHO MENTIONED FINDING

23:51.030 --> 23:52.884
A, UH, AN OLD BAR SIGN
THIS MORNING.

23:52.930 --> 23:54.022
OKAY.

23:54.060 --> 23:55.152
DOESN'T SEEM LIKE THE KIND
OF NEIGHBORHOOD WHERE PEOPLE

23:55.200 --> 23:57.589
ARE JUST THROWING OUT
OLD FURNITURE ONTO THE STREET.

23:57.630 --> 23:59.518
MAYBE SOMEBODY
HAD SOMETHING OUT FOR PICKUP,

23:59.570 --> 24:01.538
LIKE A JUNK COLLECTOR
OR CHARITY PICKUP OR SOMETHING.

24:01.570 --> 24:04.459
THEN THAT WOULD MEAN
THAT THERE WAS A VAN
IN THAT NEIGHBORHOOD TODAY,

24:04.510 --> 24:05.738
AND I WANT TO KNOW
WHO WAS DRIVING IT.

24:05.770 --> 24:08.102
RHYS WOULD KNOW THE ADDRESS OF
WHERE HE FOUND THAT HEADBOARD.

24:08.140 --> 24:09.129
GO.

24:10.750 --> 24:12.103
[ DOOR BUZZES ]
RHYS --

24:12.150 --> 24:13.003
DON'T TELL ME.

24:13.050 --> 24:14.677
YOU DIDN'T FIND THE KID
IN MY BASEMENT,

24:14.720 --> 24:15.573
BUT THERE ARE NEIGHBORS

24:15.620 --> 24:17.941
WITH TORCHES AND PITCHFORKS
ON MY LAWN.

24:17.990 --> 24:18.911
LOOK, I AM SO SORRY,

24:18.950 --> 24:20.508
BUT WE STILL NEED YOUR HELP,
ALL RIGHT?

24:20.560 --> 24:21.652
[ SIGHS ] YEAH.

24:21.690 --> 24:23.578
THE HEADBOARD THAT YOU WERE
PAINTING THIS MORNING --

24:23.630 --> 24:24.779
WHERE DID YOU FIND IT?

24:24.830 --> 24:25.785
IT WAS IN A...

24:25.830 --> 24:28.822
PILE OF JUNK AND OLD FURNITURE
ON THE SIDEWALK.

24:28.860 --> 24:29.758
DO YOU REMEMBER
WHICH HOUSE?

24:29.800 --> 24:33.327
THE O'CONNELLS --
ACROSS THE STREET, AT 119.

24:33.370 --> 24:34.496
119.

24:34.540 --> 24:37.509
[ DOOR BUZZES ]

24:37.540 --> 24:40.577
OLIVER CAN'T EVEN WIN
A ROUND OF POKER WITH THAT FACE,

24:40.610 --> 24:42.475
AND THEY SUSPECT HIM
OF THIS?

24:42.510 --> 24:43.647
I KNOW. IT'S CRAZY.

24:43.680 --> 24:45.978
THE GUY GIVES HIS LIFE
TO SAVING PEOPLE, AND NOW THIS.

24:46.010 --> 24:48.274
IT MAKES YOU WONDER
IF WE CHOSE THE RIGHT CAREERS.

24:48.320 --> 24:50.618
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

24:50.650 --> 24:54.711
OKAY, I AM INTO
AVA KLEM'S ACCOUNT.

24:54.760 --> 24:56.910
NO UPDATES
IN THE LAST FOUR MONTHS.

24:56.960 --> 25:00.828
WHAT ARE THESE OLDER POSTS --
AvaAmethyst 2019, 2023?

25:00.860 --> 25:04.660
I DON'T KNOW. MAYBE SOMETHING
TO DO WITH...VIDEO GAMES?

25:06.130 --> 25:07.495
OKAY.

25:07.540 --> 25:08.859
DEAD END?

25:08.900 --> 25:10.959
MAYBE.

25:13.070 --> 25:14.571
FAMILY SAID
THAT THEY MOVED THIS STUFF

25:14.610 --> 25:15.804
WITH A COMPANY CALLED
JUNK MATES.

25:15.840 --> 25:17.137
THEY SAY
THAT THE DRIVER ISN'T BACK.

25:17.180 --> 25:18.977
HE'S STILL AT THE ReStore
WITH THE TRUCK.

25:19.010 --> 25:19.772
OKAY. YOU READY?

25:19.810 --> 25:21.619
YEAH.
LET'S GO FIND THIS BOY.

25:24.620 --> 25:26.042
SO, EVEN IF
CHRIS KLEM IS ALIVE,

25:26.090 --> 25:28.217
THAT DOESN'T MEAN
WE'RE GONNA FIND HIM BY 6:00.

25:28.260 --> 25:29.249
HEY, GUYS.

25:29.290 --> 25:30.314
HEY.
HEY.

25:30.360 --> 25:33.625
I'M SORRY -- ARE YOU GUYS
PLAYING A VIDEO GAME?

25:33.660 --> 25:34.797
WE'RE QUESTING.

25:34.830 --> 25:36.491
WE HAVE TO KILL ALL THE MOBS
BEFORE WE CAN GET GOOD ARMOR.

25:36.530 --> 25:37.963
GOD, TRACI,
THAT'S REALLY FASCINATING.

25:38.000 --> 25:40.366
MEANWHILE, THE GUY YOU'RE
SUPPOSED TO BE TRACKING DOWN

25:40.400 --> 25:42.129
TO CLEAR OLIVER'S NAME
IS PROBABLY DEAD.

25:42.170 --> 25:44.365
OH, AVA KLEM'S NOT DEAD.

25:44.410 --> 25:45.559
SHE'S RIGHT HERE.

25:45.610 --> 25:46.668
Sam: WHAT?
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

25:46.710 --> 25:48.803
Traci: AVA POSTED
WORLD OF WARCRAFT ACHIEVEMENTS,

25:48.840 --> 25:50.137
WHICH LED DOV
TO HER GAMING ACCOUNT.

25:50.180 --> 25:52.148
HE JUST FOUND HER.
HE'S PLAYING HER RIGHT NOW.

25:52.180 --> 25:53.044
SHE'S IN THE CITY.

25:53.080 --> 25:54.968
DOV: WE TRACED
HER ROUTER I.P. ADDRESS

25:55.020 --> 25:56.009
TO THE COLLEGE AND RUSSELL
AREA.

25:56.050 --> 25:57.745
I'M STILL WAITING TO HEAR BACK
FROM HER I.S.P.,

25:57.790 --> 25:59.041
BUT IF YOU GUYS WANT
TO HEAD DOWN THERE,

25:59.090 --> 26:00.978
I'LL CALL YOU AS SOON AS I HAVE
AN EXACT LOCATION.

26:01.020 --> 26:02.954
DOV, MY APOLOGIES.
YOU'RE A ROCK STAR.

26:02.990 --> 26:04.526
ACTUALLY,
I'M A MUSCULAR ORC.

26:04.560 --> 26:05.652
DON'T KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS.

26:05.690 --> 26:08.158
JUST MAKE SURE
SHE STAYS ONLINE.

26:08.200 --> 26:09.952
KEEP HER PLAYING!

26:15.770 --> 26:18.466
[ SIREN WAILING ]

26:18.510 --> 26:20.398
[ BACKUP SIGNAL BEEPING ]

26:20.440 --> 26:21.429
HEY!

26:21.480 --> 26:23.675
YOU DO A PICKUP ON
WESTERLAND COURT THIS MORNING?

26:23.710 --> 26:24.938
YEAH.
WHY? WHAT'S UP?

26:24.980 --> 26:26.675
YOU SEE A BOY --
LITTLE BOY?

26:26.710 --> 26:28.439
NO.
IT WAS ALL FURNITURE, MAN.

26:28.480 --> 26:29.344
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:29.380 --> 26:30.984
HE'S BEEN MISSING
SINCE THIS MORNING.

26:31.020 --> 26:33.853
ALL RIGHT, MOM SAID THAT
THE KID LIKED TO READ FANTASY.

26:33.890 --> 26:35.517
UH, WHAT'D YOU PICK UP?

26:35.560 --> 26:38.358
DESK, AN OLD WARDROBE,
SOME SHELVES.

26:38.390 --> 26:40.551
YOU KNOW WHAT? I KNOW THIS BOOK.
I KNOW THIS BOOK.

26:40.590 --> 26:41.591
I READ THIS TO THE GIRLS.

26:41.630 --> 26:43.552
IT'S ABOUT A KID
WHO GOES INTO A MAGIC WARDROBE

26:43.600 --> 26:44.897
THAT TAKES HIM
TO DIFFERENT WORLDS.

26:44.930 --> 26:46.659
WHERE'S THE STUFF
THAT YOU PICKED UP TODAY?

26:46.700 --> 26:48.190
RIGHT THERE.

26:49.840 --> 26:52.365
NO!
NO, NO, NO, NO!

26:52.410 --> 26:53.365
NICK! NICK!

26:53.410 --> 26:54.536
UH, HOLD UP HERE,
ALL RIGHT?

26:54.580 --> 26:55.535
HOLD ON! STOP!
HOLD UP.

26:55.580 --> 26:57.002
EVAN?!

26:57.040 --> 26:57.802
EVAN?

26:57.850 --> 26:58.771
WHOA! WHOA!
HOLD UP! HOLD UP!

26:58.810 --> 27:01.017
SHUT IT DOWN! SHUT IT DOWN!
SHUT IT DOWN!

27:01.050 --> 27:02.608
IT'S THIS THING
RIGHT HERE, MAN.

27:02.650 --> 27:04.288
EVAN?
[ GRU NTS ]

27:04.320 --> 27:05.309
EVAN?!

27:06.620 --> 27:08.815
OKAY, IT'S JAMMED. IT'S JAMMED.
I NEED A CROWBAR OR SOMETHING.

27:08.860 --> 27:11.078
EVAN? EVAN? EVAN?!

27:11.130 --> 27:12.529
HERE, HERE, HERE.

27:12.560 --> 27:14.198
ALL RIGHT.

27:17.200 --> 27:18.690
[ GRUNTS ]

27:20.300 --> 27:21.938
GIVE ME A HAND.

27:23.040 --> 27:25.201
OH, HE'S OUT.
HE'S OUT. HE'S OUT.

27:25.240 --> 27:26.605
EVAN? EVAN?
HEY, EVAN?

27:26.640 --> 27:27.607
GONNA GRAB HIM?
YEAH.

27:27.640 --> 27:28.379
EVAN?
EVAN, BUDDY.

27:28.410 --> 27:30.378
OKAY, GET HIM UP.
GET HIM UP.

27:30.410 --> 27:31.843
WATCH HIS HEAD.
WATCH HIS HEAD.

27:31.880 --> 27:32.744
I GOT YOU.
COME ON.

27:32.780 --> 27:33.508
OKAY, I GOT HIM.
I GOT HIM. I GOT HIM.

27:33.550 --> 27:35.074
GIVE ME THOSE LEGS.
[ GRUNTS ]

27:35.120 --> 27:37.076
ALL RIGHT, CALL IT IN.
CALL IT IN, OKAY?

27:37.120 --> 27:38.917
1519. WE NEED E.M.S.
TO OUR LOCATION.

27:38.950 --> 27:41.680
WE HAVE A MALE CHILD,
8 YEARS OLD, UNCONSCIOUS.

27:41.720 --> 27:44.154
HE'S UNRESPONSIVE, NICK.
I'M GONNA START CPR.

27:44.190 --> 27:45.020
GOT HIS HEAD?

27:45.060 --> 27:45.879
[ GRUNTS ]

27:45.930 --> 27:48.455
OKAY.
EASY, EASY, EASY, EASY, EASY.

27:48.500 --> 27:49.751
DOWN. OKAY.

27:49.800 --> 27:51.165
CHECK HIS AIRWAY.

27:51.200 --> 27:52.189
UP.

27:53.400 --> 27:54.867
[ GASPS ]

27:54.900 --> 27:55.798
[ GROANS ]
ALL RIGHT.

27:55.840 --> 27:56.499
HEY, HEY, EVAN.
NO!

27:56.540 --> 27:58.633
EVAN.
HEY! HEY! HEY! HEY! HEY!

27:58.670 --> 27:59.932
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.
STOP! AAH!

27:59.970 --> 28:01.528
EASY, EASY. NO. EASY.

28:01.580 --> 28:02.899
[ GRUNTING ]
YOU KNOW WHAT?
EVAN, EVAN?

28:02.940 --> 28:05.170
I'M A -- HEY, EVAN, EVAN.
LOOK AT ME.

28:05.210 --> 28:06.177
LOOK AT ME.

28:06.210 --> 28:08.041
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

28:08.080 --> 28:09.240
IT'S OKAY.

28:09.280 --> 28:12.147
YEAH, BUDDY. YEAH, YOU'RE OKAY.
YOU'RE OKAY, EVAN.

28:12.190 --> 28:14.750
YEAH, HE'S OKAY.

28:14.790 --> 28:17.281
EVAN, I'M OLIVER.

28:17.320 --> 28:18.548
OKAY, PAL.

28:18.590 --> 28:20.148
OKAY. OKAY.

28:20.190 --> 28:21.293
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

28:21.330 --> 28:22.820
YEAH.

28:24.270 --> 28:25.225
IT'LL RING.

28:25.270 --> 28:26.464
I KNOW.

28:26.500 --> 28:28.161
SPEAKING OF RINGS...

28:28.200 --> 28:29.064
WERE WE?

28:29.100 --> 28:30.761
YOU KNOW,
THAT RING THAT I BOUGHT YOU

28:30.810 --> 28:32.607
WAS NOT
FROM A VENDING MACHINE.

28:32.640 --> 28:34.835
THAT WAS
A SIGNIFICANT PURCHASE.

28:36.010 --> 28:37.978
UH, YEAH,
YOU DON'T HAVE ANY ALLERGIES.

28:38.010 --> 28:39.944
YOU WEAR THESE LITTLE,
UH, FAKE EARRINGS EVERY DAY.

28:39.980 --> 28:42.175
SHUT UP. I KNOW.
IT'S EMBARRASSING.

28:42.220 --> 28:43.278
WHAT'S EM BARRASSING?

28:43.320 --> 28:44.309
MY EARRINGS!

28:44.350 --> 28:46.147
LOOK,
I'M NOT ALLERGIC TO...

28:46.190 --> 28:47.589
MM-HMM. MM-HMM.

28:47.620 --> 28:48.814
...CHEAP METALS.

28:48.860 --> 28:50.157
[ LAUGHS SARCASTICALLY ]

28:50.190 --> 28:52.920
THE THING IS, I'M REALLY
SENSITIVE TO PRECIOUS METALS.

28:52.960 --> 28:53.995
[ Chuckling ] OH.

28:54.030 --> 28:56.328
I'M LIKE
A REVERSE PRINCESS.

28:56.360 --> 28:57.122
A REVERSE PRINCESS.

28:57.160 --> 28:58.559
IT'S NOT GLAMOROUS.
I KNOW.

28:58.600 --> 29:00.932
YOU KNOW HOW I KICKED YOUR ASS
AT THAT PARTNER GAME?

29:00.970 --> 29:02.232
NO,
YOU DIDN'T KICK MY ASS.

29:02.270 --> 29:04.534
YEAH, WELL, UM...WE BOTH AGREE
I BUY THE BETTER GIFTS.

29:04.570 --> 29:07.733
AND YOU KNOW WHAT --
BEFORE THIS WHOLE MESS STARTED,

29:07.780 --> 29:11.147
I BOUGHT YOU THE PERFECT GIFT
AT THE DOLLAR STORE.

29:11.180 --> 29:12.704
IT'S RIGHT IN
THAT GLOVE BOX.

29:12.750 --> 29:14.843
YOU GO -- GO FOR IT.
GET IN THERE.

29:17.520 --> 29:19.340
OHH.

29:19.390 --> 29:20.379
[ LAUGHS ]

29:20.420 --> 29:22.354
OHH.
WHERE DID YOU FIND IT?

29:22.390 --> 29:24.950
YEAH. WHERE'D I FIND THAT?
IN THE BEDSHEETS.

29:24.990 --> 29:26.355
THAT LITTLE GADGET
IS AMAZING.

29:26.390 --> 29:28.529
AS LONG AS YOU WEAR YOUR RING
WITH THAT ATTACHED...

29:28.560 --> 29:29.549
ATTACHED TO IT?

29:29.600 --> 29:31.488
...YOU'LL NEVER LOSE IT
AGAIN.

29:31.530 --> 29:33.464
CHECK THIS OUT.

29:33.500 --> 29:34.694
[ WHISTLES ]

29:34.740 --> 29:36.469
[ QUACKING ]
YOU WANT ME TO WEAR IT
LIKE THIS?

29:37.270 --> 29:38.760
[ WHISTLES ]
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

29:38.810 --> 29:39.765
MCNALLY.

29:39.810 --> 29:42.472
THE I.S.P. PUTS THE COMPUTER
AVA KLEM IS USING

29:42.510 --> 29:44.205
IN THE UNIVERSITY LIBRARY.

29:44.250 --> 29:46.901
DOV, YOU KILLED IT.
THANK YOU.

29:46.950 --> 29:48.713
WE'RE HEADING TO THE UNIVERSITY
LIBRARY COMPUTERS.

29:48.750 --> 29:49.944
LET'S DO IT.

29:49.980 --> 29:51.880
YEAH, NOW IT'S MY TURN
TO GET YOU THE PERFECT GIFT.

29:51.920 --> 29:52.682
WHAT'S THAT?

29:52.720 --> 29:54.608
WHOEVER'S
SETTING UP YOUR BEST MAN

29:54.660 --> 29:55.752
ON A SILVER PLATTER.

29:55.790 --> 29:57.257
YES, PLEASE.

30:02.360 --> 30:03.497
GO THAT WAY.

30:10.640 --> 30:12.301
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

30:12.340 --> 30:15.901
EXCUSE ME. UH,
WHO SIGNED YOU ON TO THIS GAME?

30:15.940 --> 30:17.942
UH,
IT WAS JUST SOME GIRL.

30:17.980 --> 30:19.470
DO YOU KNOW AVA KLEM?

30:19.510 --> 30:21.341
NO.
SHE JUST TOOK OFF.

30:21.380 --> 30:23.018
WHAT'S HER NAM E?

30:23.050 --> 30:23.812
SAM?

30:23.850 --> 30:25.545
SAM, BEHIND YOU.

30:25.590 --> 30:26.488
HEY! HEY, HEY!

30:26.520 --> 30:28.385
STOP! HEY!

30:28.420 --> 30:29.455
STOP!

30:38.300 --> 30:39.267
WHOA! WHOA!

30:39.970 --> 30:41.130
HEY! GO! GO! GO!

30:48.240 --> 30:50.071
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
DON'T KILL ME!

30:50.110 --> 30:52.772
AVA, IT'S OKAY.
WE'RE NOT GONNA HURT YOU.

30:52.810 --> 30:54.209
WE JUST HAVE
A COUPLE OF QUESTIONS.

30:54.250 --> 30:55.774
I KNOW
YOU'RE NOT REAL COPS,

30:55.820 --> 30:57.173
AND I KNOW
YOU'RE GOING TO KILL ME.

30:57.220 --> 30:59.108
WHAT?
[ WHISTLE BLOWING ]

30:59.150 --> 31:00.708
NO! NO! NO! NO! NO! NO!
NO! NO! NO! IT'S --

31:00.750 --> 31:02.684
NO!
IT'S -- IT'S OKAY!

31:02.720 --> 31:05.450
[ WHISTLE CONTINUES BLOWING ]
AVA. AVA.
AVA, CAN YOU JUST...

31:06.530 --> 31:08.088
OKAY, OKAY. OKAY!

31:10.970 --> 31:12.062
I'M NOT GETTING INTO
A SQUAD CAR.

31:12.100 --> 31:12.896
OKAY. YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

31:12.930 --> 31:14.238
YOU JUST NEED
TO CALL YOUR FATHER.

31:14.270 --> 31:15.794
I CAN'T CALL HIM,
OFFICER MURDERER.

31:15.840 --> 31:17.068
OBVIOUSLY,
HE TOSSED HIS PHONE

31:17.100 --> 31:19.239
THE MINUTE
I ACTIVATED THE PLAN.

31:19.270 --> 31:20.237
WHAT PLAN?

31:20.270 --> 31:21.168
HEY!

31:21.210 --> 31:22.905
DOES ANYONE HAVE A CAMERA
ON THEIR PHONE?

31:22.940 --> 31:24.441
BECAUSE THESE ARE NOT
OFFICERS OF THE LAW!

31:24.480 --> 31:26.038
OKAY.
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT,
CALM DOWN.

31:26.080 --> 31:28.116
I DEMAND TO KNOW
THE CHARGES AGAINST ME!

31:28.150 --> 31:29.515
WHAT ARE THE CHARGES
AGAINST THIS GIRL?

31:29.550 --> 31:30.642
NOTHING.

31:30.680 --> 31:31.817
THERE ARE NO CHARGES
AGAINST HER.

31:31.850 --> 31:32.885
WE ARE TRYING
TO FIND YOUR FATHER.

31:32.920 --> 31:36.185
JUST SHOW US YOUR BADGE.
I BET IT'S NOT EVEN REAL.

31:38.690 --> 31:39.918
HOW DO WE KNOW
THAT'S NOT A FAKE BADGE?

31:39.960 --> 31:41.120
WE ARE POLICE OFFICERS.

31:41.160 --> 31:43.890
AVA, WE'RE NOT HERE TO HURT YOU.
WE NEED YOUR HELP -- PLEASE.

31:43.930 --> 31:45.124
DON'T BELIEVE THEM.

31:45.170 --> 31:47.491
THEY'RE TAKING ME
AGAINST MY WILL!

31:47.530 --> 31:48.758
WE'RE NOT TAKING YOU.

31:48.800 --> 31:50.165
WE REALLY JUST WANT
TO HELP YOU, OKAY?

31:50.200 --> 31:51.906
WE NEED TO FIND YOUR DAD.

31:51.940 --> 31:53.669
PLEASE.

31:53.710 --> 31:54.734
SHOULD YOU
BE TOUCHING HER?

31:54.780 --> 31:55.769
I'M NOT TOUCHING HER.

31:55.810 --> 31:56.834
YOU'RE VERY IRRITATING!

31:56.880 --> 31:57.972
HOLD -- JUST...

31:58.010 --> 31:59.648
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

31:59.680 --> 32:00.874
AVA!

32:00.910 --> 32:02.616
COME ON. COME ON.
LET'S GO. LET'S GO.

32:02.650 --> 32:03.639
I'M SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY.

32:03.680 --> 32:05.341
NO, NO, NO, NO. IT'S OKAY.
SWEETHEART, IT'S OKAY.

32:05.390 --> 32:08.154
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.
IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT, OKAY?

32:08.190 --> 32:11.057
MR. KLEM?
CHRIS KLEM?

32:11.090 --> 32:12.182
YOU GOT A WARRANT?

32:12.230 --> 32:14.619
WE -- WE DON'T HAVE A WARRANT.
WE JUST WANT TO TALK.

32:14.660 --> 32:15.558
NO WARRANT.
NO WARRANT!

32:15.600 --> 32:17.090
OKAY, WE'RE LEAVING.
ALL RIGHT, CALM DOWN.

32:17.130 --> 32:18.791
WHO -- WHO --
WHO'S CHASING YOU?
[ LAUGHS ]

32:18.830 --> 32:20.024
WHY ARE YOU RUNNING?
YOU KNOW. YOU KNOW.

32:20.070 --> 32:20.968
Y-YOU'RE IN ON IT!

32:21.000 --> 32:23.434
WE'RE NOT IN ON ANYTHING.
LISTEN TO ME.

32:23.470 --> 32:25.700
I'M DETECTIVE SWAREK.
THIS IS OFFICER MCNALLY.

32:25.740 --> 32:27.503
MR. KLEM...

32:27.540 --> 32:29.974
WE BELIEVE THE PERSON
WHO'S THREATENING YOU

32:30.010 --> 32:32.740
IS ALSO TRYING
TO FRAME OUR FRIEND.

32:32.780 --> 32:35.317
OKAY? OUR COLLEAGUE.

32:36.420 --> 32:37.170
OKAY, AVA...

32:37.220 --> 32:39.780
IT'S TIME TO GO --
RIGHT NOW, OKAY?

32:39.820 --> 32:40.912
YOU KNOW WHO TO CALL.
YOU KNOW THE PLAN.

32:40.950 --> 32:42.383
I'M NOT LEAVING.
THEY WANT ME, NOT YOU!

32:42.420 --> 32:44.752
JUST CALM DOWN. CALM DOWN,
ALL RIGHT? JUST CALM.

32:44.790 --> 32:45.882
OKAY,
AVA, MR. KLEM,

32:45.930 --> 32:47.955
IF WE WERE COMING AFTER YOU,
IS THIS WHERE WE'D DO IT --

32:48.000 --> 32:50.059
IN FRONT OF ALL THESE PEOPLE,
IN LIBRARY?

32:56.070 --> 32:58.607
I FEEL LIKE
I'M LOSING MY MIND.

32:58.640 --> 33:01.131
Andy:
YOU'RE NOT LOSING YOUR MIND.
WE BELIEVE YOU.

33:01.180 --> 33:04.047
WE NEED TO KNOW
WHO'S THREATENING YOU.

33:04.080 --> 33:07.208
[ SIGHS ]

33:08.950 --> 33:11.339
WE KNOW
IT WAS A POLICE OFFICER.

33:11.390 --> 33:12.448
WE KNOW THAT.

33:13.850 --> 33:15.681
OKAY.

33:15.720 --> 33:17.187
THIS GUY CALLED ME.

33:17.220 --> 33:19.029
HE SAID
HE WANTED COMPONENTS --

33:19.060 --> 33:20.550
A DET CORD
AND EXPLOSIVES.

33:20.590 --> 33:22.990
SAID IT WAS
FOR A TRAINING EXERCISE.

33:23.030 --> 33:25.021
I BROUGHT IT TO HIM,
AND HE SHOWED ME HIS BADGE,

33:25.070 --> 33:26.662
BUT HE SAID
HE WAS IN THIS BIG RUSH

33:26.700 --> 33:28.133
AND HE HAD TO GO
RIGHT AWAY,

33:28.170 --> 33:29.933
SO I DIDN'T FILL OUT
THE PAPERWORK.

33:29.970 --> 33:31.335
SO YOU GAVE IT TO HIM?

33:31.370 --> 33:34.339
YEAH, IT WAS STUPID,
BUT HE WAS A POLICE OFFICER.

33:34.380 --> 33:36.530
I WORK
WITH POLICE OFFICERS.

33:36.580 --> 33:37.638
CALM DOWN.

33:37.680 --> 33:39.568
GO ON.

33:42.280 --> 33:44.419
THAT NIGHT, I HEARD ABOUT
THE EXPLOSION AT 15 DIVISION,

33:44.450 --> 33:47.578
SO I CALLED THE NUMBER
TO SEE WHAT HAPPENED, AND...

33:47.620 --> 33:48.917
IT WAS OUT OF SERVICE.

33:48.960 --> 33:49.915
[ SNIFFLES ]

33:49.960 --> 33:50.949
THE NEXT DAY,

33:50.990 --> 33:53.049
SOME WOMAN COP PICKS ME UP
ON THE SIDE OF THE ROAD,

33:53.090 --> 33:54.557
SAYING
THAT I HAVE COCAINE ON ME.

33:54.600 --> 33:57.694
I-I'M 15.
I'VE NEVER EVEN SEEN COCAINE.

33:58.970 --> 34:02.337
IT WAS A THREAT,
WHICH WE TOOK SERIOUSLY,

34:02.370 --> 34:04.429
AND WE LEFT THAT NIGHT.

34:05.940 --> 34:07.362
WE'VE BEEN RUNNING
EVER SINCE.

34:07.410 --> 34:08.434
OKAY.

34:08.480 --> 34:12.177
CHRIS, THE OFFICER
YOU SOLD THE EXPLOSIVES TO --

34:12.210 --> 34:13.802
WHAT DID HE LOOK LIKE?

34:13.850 --> 34:15.010
NO. I CAN'T.

34:15.050 --> 34:17.268
NO. IF I TELL YOU THAT,
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN TO US THEN?

34:17.320 --> 34:20.778
WE'RE GONNA PUT YOU INTO
A SAFE HOUSE TONIGHT. I PROMISE.

34:20.820 --> 34:23.755
BUT WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME,
AND WE NEED A NAME.

34:23.790 --> 34:25.121
PLEASE.

34:31.800 --> 34:34.064
OLIVER SHAW.

34:34.100 --> 34:36.466
HIS NAME WAS OLIVER SHAW.

34:46.250 --> 34:48.275
[ SIREN CHIRPS ]

34:50.620 --> 34:51.541
HEY.

34:51.590 --> 34:52.739
HEY.

34:52.790 --> 34:54.348
HEY, CHECK THIS OUT.

34:54.390 --> 34:55.687
ANOTHER ROUGH DAY
IN THE WHITE SHIRT.

34:55.720 --> 34:57.688
* ANOTHER ROUGH DAY

34:57.720 --> 34:58.721
[ CHUCKLES ]
ALL RIGHT.

34:58.760 --> 35:00.785
IZZY'S GIG IS IN AN HOUR,
SO I'M THINKING

35:00.830 --> 35:03.196
MAYBE I SHOULD JUST
TAKE IT DOWN THERE, RIGHT?

35:03.230 --> 35:05.164
I COULD ROCK THIS.
COULD YOU JUST PLEASE
TELL HIM?

35:05.200 --> 35:06.189
OKAY.
NOW, ANDY --

35:06.230 --> 35:07.492
UM, OLIVER.

35:07.530 --> 35:08.736
YES?

35:08.770 --> 35:11.159
THERE'S BEEN
AN INTERNAL AFFAIRS OFFICER

35:11.210 --> 35:13.235
CONDUCTING AN INVESTIGATION

35:13.270 --> 35:15.932
I-INTO SERIOUS CORRUPTION
IN OUR DIVISION,

35:15.980 --> 35:20.076
AND SOMEONE HAS CONNECTED YOU
WITH THE EVIDENCE-ROOM BOMB.

35:20.110 --> 35:21.646
WAIT. WHOA. WHOA.
STOP. STOP.

35:23.780 --> 35:24.815
WAIT. UH...

35:24.850 --> 35:29.219
THE EXPLOSIVES BROKER SAID
OLIVER SHAW PICKED IT UP.

35:33.390 --> 35:34.254
I-I BOUGHT THE EXPLOSIVES?

35:34.300 --> 35:36.996
WE KNOW IT IS NOT
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

35:37.030 --> 35:38.429
WHAT --

35:38.470 --> 35:39.425
OKAY.

35:39.470 --> 35:40.994
WAIT.

35:41.030 --> 35:43.635
CAN YOU TELL ME
WHAT IT LOOKS...LIKE?

35:43.670 --> 35:44.637
OKAY.

35:44.670 --> 35:48.333
AS FAR AS I.A. IS CONCERNED,
THEY'RE GONNA SEE

35:48.380 --> 35:50.371
YOU'VE HAD FINANCIAL TROUBLES
SINCE THE DIVORCE,

35:50.410 --> 35:52.241
BUT YOU'RE SPENDING MONEY
LIKE CRAZY,

35:52.280 --> 35:53.645
YOU'VE HAD
A NICE PROMOTION,

35:53.680 --> 35:55.671
YOUR KEY CARD WAS USED
IN THE EVIDENCE ROOM

35:55.720 --> 35:57.369
THE DAY OF THE BOMBING,
EVEN THOUGH

35:57.420 --> 35:59.911
YOU DIDN'T MAKE ANY ARRESTS,
DIDN'T CHECK IN ANY EVIDENCE.

36:01.790 --> 36:03.758
I'VE BEEN SPENDING MONEY
LIKE IT'S GOING OUT OF STYLE

36:03.790 --> 36:06.588
SINCE THE DIVORCE
BECAUSE I'M GETTING A DIVORCE.

36:06.630 --> 36:07.528
THAT'S HOW IT WORKS.

36:07.560 --> 36:10.757
THERE'S --
THERE'S IZZY'S DRUG CHARGE.

36:10.800 --> 36:12.768
IT DISAPPEARED.

36:17.440 --> 36:19.260
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

36:20.710 --> 36:23.031
THERE'S A REPORT
GOING IN TO ALONSO SANTANA

36:23.080 --> 36:25.071
RIGHT --
RIGHT ABOUT NOW...

36:25.110 --> 36:27.840
IMPLICATING YOU
IN THE BOMBING.

36:30.980 --> 36:33.084
[ IZZY TALKING INDISTINCT LY ]

36:33.120 --> 36:34.212
[ DOOR OPENS ]

36:34.260 --> 36:35.557
OKAY, BUT I GOT TO GO.

36:35.590 --> 36:37.785
OKAY. BYE, MOM.
BYE-BYE.

36:39.690 --> 36:40.987
WHAT?

36:41.030 --> 36:42.588
HI, BABY.

36:42.630 --> 36:43.392
HI.

36:43.430 --> 36:44.988
OKAY, WELL --
[ SIGHS ]

36:45.030 --> 36:47.396
YOU KNOW WHAT? NO.

36:47.430 --> 36:49.136
I JUST -- THERE --
IT'S...

36:49.170 --> 36:50.865
HOW LONG
HAVE I DONE THIS JOB?

36:50.900 --> 36:53.607
20 YEARS, I HAVE...

36:53.640 --> 36:56.905
20 YEARS, I'VE BEEN
BUSTING IN DOORS TO METH HOUSES

36:56.940 --> 36:58.373
AND BUSTING INTO BASEMENTS,

36:58.410 --> 37:00.674
AND I DON'T KNOW IF I'M GONNA
GET SHOT BY SOME SKID

37:00.710 --> 37:04.248
OR IF I'M EVER GONNA
SEE MY KIDS' FACES AGAIN.

37:04.290 --> 37:06.349
DADDY, WHAT HAPPENED
TO YOUR SHIRT?

37:10.420 --> 37:12.650
I SAVED A KID TODAY.

37:12.690 --> 37:13.725
OKAY.

37:13.760 --> 37:15.648
BUTKID...

37:15.700 --> 37:16.758
[ SIGHS ]

37:16.800 --> 37:17.926
...MY GIRL...

37:17.960 --> 37:19.928
WHO GREW UP WITH THE SAME HOPES
AND THE SAME DREAMS

37:19.970 --> 37:22.837
AS EVERY OTHER LITTLE KID --
WHAT DOES SHE GET?

37:22.870 --> 37:25.862
SHE GETS TO WAKE UP WITH TEETH
STILL UNDER HER PILLOW

37:25.910 --> 37:28.208
AND A DAD WHO DIDN'T SEE
ANY OF HER -- WHAT IS IT? --

37:28.240 --> 37:30.037
62 HOME RUNS.

37:30.080 --> 37:31.809
BECAUSE I'M A COP,
RIGHT?

37:31.850 --> 37:33.704
BECAUSE
I'M PART OF THE BROTHERHOOD --

37:33.750 --> 37:34.978
BROTHERHOOD
FOR THE GREATER GOOD.

37:35.020 --> 37:37.648
WHAT IS THAT THING?
THERE'S THIS THING
THEY SAY, DARLING.

37:37.680 --> 37:38.840
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:38.890 --> 37:41.757
IT'S, UH, "MISSING SOLOS,
BUT SAVING THE WORLD," RIGHT?

37:41.790 --> 37:42.882
THAT'S ME.

37:42.920 --> 37:45.184
AND THEN I GET -- YOU GUYS
HAVE TO COME AND TELL ME THIS.

37:45.230 --> 37:46.857
[ TAPPING DESK ]

37:46.890 --> 37:48.221
THAT'S WHAT I GET.

37:48.260 --> 37:50.956
ARE THEY GONNA ARREST ME?

37:56.200 --> 37:57.599
BROTHER,
THEY'RE GONNA BURY YOU.

37:57.640 --> 37:59.562
[Voice breaking ]
THEY'RE GONNA TRY.

38:07.250 --> 38:09.411
YEAH. YEAH.
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

38:09.450 --> 38:11.213
I WANT YOU
TO GIVE THIS TO JARVIS FOR ME.

38:11.250 --> 38:12.239
NO!

38:12.290 --> 38:13.382
OLIVER, DON'T, OKAY?

38:13.420 --> 38:16.150
THERE'S -- THERE'S GOT TO BE
SOME WAY TO FIGURE THIS OUT.

38:16.190 --> 38:17.817
HEY, I'M GONNA, UH,
I'M GONNA GO.

38:17.860 --> 38:21.728
I GOT TO -- I'M GONNA --
I'M GONNA DRUM IN MY KID'S BAND.

38:21.760 --> 38:23.250
THAT'S WHAT I'M GONNA DO.
COME ON, BABY.

38:23.300 --> 38:24.858
YEAH? ARE YOU SURE?

38:24.900 --> 38:26.265
YES. YEAH.

38:26.300 --> 38:28.063
YEAH.

38:32.070 --> 38:33.958
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:50.060 --> 38:52.255
YOU WERE WAITING
FOR PASSPORTS?

38:52.290 --> 38:54.429
YEAH.

38:54.460 --> 38:57.190
I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE TO START.

38:57.230 --> 39:01.291
BUT I'M A NERD,
SO I THOUGHT BOOKS.

39:01.330 --> 39:04.766
WE RESEARCHED
HOW TO DISAPPEAR.

39:04.810 --> 39:07.699
THE LIBRARY KIND OF BECAME
A COMMAND CENTER.

39:07.740 --> 39:09.537
BUT HOW DID YOU GET
BIRTH CERTIFICATES?

39:09.580 --> 39:12.003
I CALLED PEOPLE
AND SAID I WAS GOVERNMENT,

39:12.050 --> 39:14.439
TOLD THEM
THERE WAS A FIRE,

39:14.480 --> 39:17.574
AND THEY HAD TO MAIL IN
THEIR BIRTH CERTIFICATES

39:17.620 --> 39:21.454
IN ORDER FOR US
TO RE-REGISTER THEM AND...

39:21.490 --> 39:24.152
MOST PEOPLE DIDN'T.
BUT...

39:24.190 --> 39:25.953
SOME PEOPLE DID.

39:25.990 --> 39:27.958
WHAT DO YOU KNOW.

39:27.990 --> 39:30.754
WE HAD SOME MONEY
UNDER THE MATTRESS --

39:30.800 --> 39:33.928
MY WIFE'S
RAINY-DAY FUND.

39:33.970 --> 39:35.995
I LEFT HER ASHES.

39:38.200 --> 39:41.579
I COULDN'T RISK ANYONE KNOWING
THAT, UH, WE WERE ALIVE,

39:41.610 --> 39:42.429
SO...

39:42.480 --> 39:44.971
WE EVEN LEFT TARZAN.

39:45.010 --> 39:48.070
PUT HIM IN THE BACKYARD
AND WALKED OUT.

39:49.820 --> 39:50.673
IS HE OKAY?

39:50.720 --> 39:54.110
YEAH. HE'S FINE.
HE'S WITH YOUR NEIGHBOR.

40:06.100 --> 40:07.692
[ SIGHS ]

40:13.370 --> 40:14.678
YOU SEEN NASH?

40:14.710 --> 40:16.575
NO?

40:18.340 --> 40:20.399
I'M SORRY...

40:20.450 --> 40:21.872
ABOUT EVERYTHING.

40:21.920 --> 40:23.649
I JUST...

40:23.680 --> 40:25.238
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO.

40:25.290 --> 40:27.508
I UNDERSTAND.

40:27.550 --> 40:29.450
I MEAN, I HAVE A SON.

40:29.490 --> 40:32.186
I WOULD DO ANYTHING I HAD TO
TO PROTECT HIM.

40:32.230 --> 40:33.857
EVEN FROM THE POLICE?

40:33.890 --> 40:34.925
YEAH.

40:34.960 --> 40:37.428
IF THEY'RE DIRTY, YEAH.

40:37.460 --> 40:39.519
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

40:39.570 --> 40:41.219
WHAT'S GOING ON?

40:41.270 --> 40:42.396
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

40:42.440 --> 40:43.737
THAT'S HIM.

40:43.770 --> 40:45.931
THAT'S THE COP
WHO BOUGHT THE BOMB.

40:45.970 --> 40:47.232
THAT'S HIS FACE.

40:47.270 --> 40:49.431
THAT'S OLIVER SHAW.

40:50.380 --> 40:53.577
WHY IS HE CALLING YOU?

40:53.610 --> 40:54.770
WHY IS HE CALLING YOU?

40:54.820 --> 40:57.812
* BROKEN WINDOWS,
BROKEN DOORS *

40:57.850 --> 41:01.752
* BROKEN PEOPLE, BROKEN LAWS

41:01.790 --> 41:05.487
* BROKEN FLOWERS ON A GRAVE

41:05.530 --> 41:09.955
* BROKEN PROMISES
THAT YOU MADE *

41:13.500 --> 41:15.536
OH, FINALLY!

41:15.570 --> 41:17.231
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

41:17.270 --> 41:18.760
UH, ANDY NEEDED ME.

41:18.810 --> 41:20.766
I'VE BEEN TRYING
TO CALL YOU.

41:20.810 --> 41:24.200
SORRY. I, UM,
I TURNED MY RINGER OFF.

41:24.240 --> 41:25.207
OH.

41:25.250 --> 41:27.172
[ SIGHS ]

41:29.380 --> 41:30.677
EVERYTHING OKAY?

41:30.720 --> 41:32.085
YEAH.

41:32.120 --> 41:33.212
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:33.250 --> 41:34.558
GOOD,
'CAUSE I'M STARVING,

41:34.590 --> 41:36.148
AND THEY'RE HOLDING
OUR RESERVATION.

41:36.190 --> 41:39.023
AND I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU LOVE THE CRAZY GRILL, TRACE,

41:39.060 --> 41:40.857
BUT -- BUT EVERY TIME
WE LEAVE THERE,

41:40.890 --> 41:44.155
WE SMELL LIKE THE CRAZY GRILL,
ALL RIGHT?

41:44.200 --> 41:45.963
I MEAN...
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:46.000 --> 41:48.992
SO, ARE YOU, UM...

41:49.040 --> 41:52.464
ARE YOU SURE YOU'RE WILLING
TO PAY THAT PRICE?

41:52.510 --> 41:53.568
* BROKEN STREET

41:53.610 --> 41:57.137
* BROKEN DREAMS AS YOU AWAKE

41:57.180 --> 41:58.408
MMM.

41:58.440 --> 42:00.749
* BROKEN CHAINS
THAT BREAK TOO LATE *

42:00.780 --> 42:03.874
THERE'S ALWAYS A PRICE,
ISN'T THERE?

42:08.050 --> 42:09.153
* OHHHHHHH

42:09.190 --> 42:10.282
SHALL WE?

42:11.490 --> 42:12.457
WE SHALL.

42:12.490 --> 42:13.525
GREAT.

42:13.560 --> 42:17.621
* HERE COMES THE STORM
